1925float Simulator::canonicalizeNaN(float value) {
1926 // Default NaN value, see "NaN handling" in "IEEE 754 standard implementation
1927 // choices" of the ARM Reference Manual.
1928 constexpr uint32_t kDefaultNaN = 0x7FC00000u;
1929 if (FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ && std::isnan(value)) {
1930 value = base::bit_cast<float>(kDefaultNaN);
1931 }
1932 return value;
1933}
1934
1935Float32 Simulator::canonicalizeNaN(Float32 value) {
1936 // Default NaN value, see "NaN handling" in "IEEE 754 standard implementation
1937 // choices" of the ARM Reference Manual.
1938 constexpr Float32 kDefaultNaN = Float32::FromBits(0x7FC00000u);
1939 return FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ && value.is_nan() ? kDefaultNaN : value;
1940}
1941
1942double Simulator::canonicalizeNaN(double value) {
1943 // Default NaN value, see "NaN handling" in "IEEE 754 standard implementation
1944 // choices" of the ARM Reference Manual.
1945 constexpr uint64_t kDefaultNaN = uint64_t{0x7FF8000000000000};
1946 if (FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ && std::isnan(value)) {
1947 value = base::bit_cast<double>(kDefaultNaN);
1948 }
1949 return value;
1950}
1951
1952Float64 Simulator::canonicalizeNaN(Float64 value) {
1953 // Default NaN value, see "NaN handling" in "IEEE 754 standard implementation
1954 // choices" of the ARM Reference Manual.
1955 constexpr Float64 kDefaultNaN =
1956 Float64::FromBits(uint64_t{0x7FF8000000000000});
1957 return FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ && value.is_nan() ? kDefaultNaN : value;
1958}
1959
1960// Stop helper functions.
1961bool Simulator::isWatchedStop(uint32_t code) {
1962 DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
1963 return code < kNumOfWatchedStops;
1964}
1965
1966bool Simulator::isEnabledStop(uint32_t code) {
1967 DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
1968 // Unwatched stops are always enabled.
1969 return !isWatchedStop(code) ||
1970 !(watched_stops_[code].count & kStopDisabledBit);
1971}
1972
1973void Simulator::EnableStop(uint32_t code) {
1974 DCHECK(isWatchedStop(code));
1975 if (!isEnabledStop(code)) {
1976 watched_stops_[code].count &= ~kStopDisabledBit;
1977 }
1978}
1979
1980void Simulator::DisableStop(uint32_t code) {
1981 DCHECK(isWatchedStop(code));
1982 if (isEnabledStop(code)) {
1983 watched_stops_[code].count |= kStopDisabledBit;
1984 }
1985}
1986
1987void Simulator::IncreaseStopCounter(uint32_t code) {
1988 DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
1989 DCHECK(isWatchedStop(code));
1990 if ((watched_stops_[code].count & ~(1 << 31)) == 0x7FFFFFFF) {
1991 PrintF(
1992 "Stop counter for code %i has overflowed.\n"
1993 "Enabling this code and reseting the counter to 0.\n",
1994 code);
1995 watched_stops_[code].count = 0;
1996 EnableStop(code);
1997 } else {
1998 watched_stops_[code].count++;
1999 }
2000}
2001
2002// Print a stop status.
2003void Simulator::PrintStopInfo(uint32_t code) {
2004 DCHECK_LE(code, kMaxStopCode);
2005 if (!isWatchedStop(code)) {
2006 PrintF("Stop not watched.");
2007 } else {
2008 const char* state = isEnabledStop(code) ? "Enabled" : "Disabled";
2009 int32_t count = watched_stops_[code].count & ~kStopDisabledBit;
2010 // Don't print the state of unused breakpoints.
2011 if (count != 0) {
2012 if (watched_stops_[code].desc) {
2013 PrintF("stop %i - 0x%x: \t%s, \tcounter = %i, \t%s\n", code, code,
2014 state, count, watched_stops_[code].desc);
2015 } else {
2016 PrintF("stop %i - 0x%x: \t%s, \tcounter = %i\n", code, code, state,
2017 count);
2018 }
2019 }
2020 }
2021}
2022
2023// Handle execution based on instruction types.
2024
2025// Instruction types 0 and 1 are both rolled into one function because they
2026// only differ in the handling of the shifter_operand.
2027void Simulator::DecodeType01(Instruction* instr) {
2028 int type = instr->TypeValue();
2029 if ((type == 0) && instr->IsSpecialType0()) {
2030 // multiply instruction or extra loads and stores
2031 if (instr->Bits(7, 4) == 9) {
2032 if (instr->Bit(24) == 0) {
2033 // Raw field decoding here. Multiply instructions have their Rd in
2034 // funny places.
2035 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2036 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2037 int rs = instr->RsValue();
2038 int32_t rs_val = get_register(rs);
2039 int32_t rm_val = get_register(rm);
2040 if (instr->Bit(23) == 0) {
2041 if (instr->Bit(21) == 0) {
2042 // The MUL instruction description (A 4.1.33) refers to Rd as being
2043 // the destination for the operation, but it confusingly uses the
2044 // Rn field to encode it.
2045 // Format(instr, "mul'cond's 'rn, 'rm, 'rs");
2046 int rd = rn; // Remap the rn field to the Rd register.
2047 int32_t alu_out = base::MulWithWraparound(rm_val, rs_val);
2048 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2049 if (instr->HasS()) {
2050 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2051 }
2052 } else {
2053 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2054 int32_t acc_value = get_register(rd);
2055 if (instr->Bit(22) == 0) {
2056 // The MLA instruction description (A 4.1.28) refers to the order
2057 // of registers as "Rd, Rm, Rs, Rn". But confusingly it uses the
2058 // Rn field to encode the Rd register and the Rd field to encode
2059 // the Rn register.
2060 // Format(instr, "mla'cond's 'rn, 'rm, 'rs, 'rd");
2061 int32_t mul_out = base::MulWithWraparound(rm_val, rs_val);
2062 int32_t result = base::AddWithWraparound(acc_value, mul_out);
2063 set_register(rn, result);
2064 } else {
2065 // Format(instr, "mls'cond's 'rn, 'rm, 'rs, 'rd");
2066 int32_t mul_out = base::MulWithWraparound(rm_val, rs_val);
2067 int32_t result = base::SubWithWraparound(acc_value, mul_out);
2068 set_register(rn, result);
2069 }
2070 }
2071 } else {
2072 // The signed/long multiply instructions use the terms RdHi and RdLo
2073 // when referring to the target registers. They are mapped to the Rn
2074 // and Rd fields as follows:
2075 // RdLo == Rd
2076 // RdHi == Rn (This is confusingly stored in variable rd here
2077 // because the mul instruction from above uses the
2078 // Rn field to encode the Rd register. Good luck figuring
2079 // this out without reading the ARM instruction manual
2080 // at a very detailed level.)
2081 // Format(instr, "'um'al'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'rs, 'rm");
2082 int rd_hi = rn; // Remap the rn field to the RdHi register.
2083 int rd_lo = instr->RdValue();
2084 int32_t hi_res = 0;
2085 int32_t lo_res = 0;
2086 if (instr->Bit(22) == 1) {
2087 int64_t left_op = static_cast<int32_t>(rm_val);
2088 int64_t right_op = static_cast<int32_t>(rs_val);
2089 uint64_t result = left_op * right_op;
2090 hi_res = static_cast<int32_t>(result >> 32);
2091 lo_res = static_cast<int32_t>(result & 0xFFFFFFFF);
2092 } else {
2093 // unsigned multiply
2094 uint64_t left_op = static_cast<uint32_t>(rm_val);
2095 uint64_t right_op = static_cast<uint32_t>(rs_val);
2096 uint64_t result = left_op * right_op;
2097 hi_res = static_cast<int32_t>(result >> 32);
2098 lo_res = static_cast<int32_t>(result & 0xFFFFFFFF);
2099 }
2100 set_register(rd_lo, lo_res);
2101 set_register(rd_hi, hi_res);
2102 if (instr->HasS()) {
2103 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2104 }
2105 }
2106 } else {
2107 if (instr->Bits(24, 23) == 3) {
2108 if (instr->Bit(20) == 1) {
2109 // ldrex
2110 int rt = instr->RtValue();
2111 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2112 int32_t addr = get_register(rn);
2113 switch (instr->Bits(22, 21)) {
2114 case 0: {
2115 // Format(instr, "ldrex'cond 'rt, ['rn]");
2116 int value = ReadExW(addr);
2117 set_register(rt, value);
2118 break;
2119 }
2120 case 1: {
2121 // Format(instr, "ldrexd'cond 'rt, ['rn]");
2122 int* rn_data = ReadExDW(addr);
2123 set_dw_register(rt, rn_data);
2124 break;
2125 }
2126 case 2: {
2127 // Format(instr, "ldrexb'cond 'rt, ['rn]");
2128 uint8_t value = ReadExBU(addr);
2129 set_register(rt, value);
2130 break;
2131 }
2132 case 3: {
2133 // Format(instr, "ldrexh'cond 'rt, ['rn]");
2134 uint16_t value = ReadExHU(addr);
2135 set_register(rt, value);
2136 break;
2137 }
2138 default:
2139 UNREACHABLE();
2140 }
2141 } else {
2142 // The instruction is documented as strex rd, rt, [rn], but the
2143 // "rt" register is using the rm bits.
2144 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2145 int rt = instr->RmValue();
2146 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2147 DCHECK_NE(rd, rn);
2148 DCHECK_NE(rd, rt);
2149 int32_t addr = get_register(rn);
2150 switch (instr->Bits(22, 21)) {
2151 case 0: {
2152 // Format(instr, "strex'cond 'rd, 'rm, ['rn]");
2153 int value = get_register(rt);
2154 int status = WriteExW(addr, value);
2155 set_register(rd, status);
2156 break;
2157 }
2158 case 1: {
2159 // Format(instr, "strexd'cond 'rd, 'rm, ['rn]");
2160 DCHECK_EQ(rt % 2, 0);
2161 int32_t value1 = get_register(rt);
2162 int32_t value2 = get_register(rt + 1);
2163 int status = WriteExDW(addr, value1, value2);
2164 set_register(rd, status);
2165 break;
2166 }
2167 case 2: {
2168 // Format(instr, "strexb'cond 'rd, 'rm, ['rn]");
2169 uint8_t value = get_register(rt);
2170 int status = WriteExB(addr, value);
2171 set_register(rd, status);
2172 break;
2173 }
2174 case 3: {
2175 // Format(instr, "strexh'cond 'rd, 'rm, ['rn]");
2176 uint16_t value = get_register(rt);
2177 int status = WriteExH(addr, value);
2178 set_register(rd, status);
2179 break;
2180 }
2181 default:
2182 UNREACHABLE();
2183 }
2184 }
2185 } else {
2186 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
2187 }
2188 }
2189 } else {
2190 // extra load/store instructions
2191 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2192 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2193 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2194 int32_t addr = 0;
2195 if (instr->Bit(22) == 0) {
2196 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2197 int32_t rm_val = get_register(rm);
2198 switch (instr->PUField()) {
2199 case da_x: {
2200 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn], -'rm");
2201 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2202 addr = rn_val;
2203 rn_val = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, rm_val);
2204 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2205 break;
2206 }
2207 case ia_x: {
2208 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn], +'rm");
2209 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2210 addr = rn_val;
2211 rn_val = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, rm_val);
2212 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2213 break;
2214 }
2215 case db_x: {
2216 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn, -'rm]'w");
2217 rn_val = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, rm_val);
2218 addr = rn_val;
2219 if (instr->HasW()) {
2220 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2221 }
2222 break;
2223 }
2224 case ib_x: {
2225 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn, +'rm]'w");
2226 rn_val = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, rm_val);
2227 addr = rn_val;
2228 if (instr->HasW()) {
2229 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2230 }
2231 break;
2232 }
2233 default: {
2234 // The PU field is a 2-bit field.
2235 UNREACHABLE();
2236 }
2237 }
2238 } else {
2239 int32_t imm_val = (instr->ImmedHValue() << 4) | instr->ImmedLValue();
2240 switch (instr->PUField()) {
2241 case da_x: {
2242 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn], #-'off8");
2243 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2244 addr = rn_val;
2245 rn_val = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, imm_val);
2246 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2247 break;
2248 }
2249 case ia_x: {
2250 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn], #+'off8");
2251 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2252 addr = rn_val;
2253 rn_val = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, imm_val);
2254 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2255 break;
2256 }
2257 case db_x: {
2258 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn, #-'off8]'w");
2259 rn_val = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, imm_val);
2260 addr = rn_val;
2261 if (instr->HasW()) {
2262 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2263 }
2264 break;
2265 }
2266 case ib_x: {
2267 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'sign'h 'rd, ['rn, #+'off8]'w");
2268 rn_val = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, imm_val);
2269 addr = rn_val;
2270 if (instr->HasW()) {
2271 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2272 }
2273 break;
2274 }
2275 default: {
2276 // The PU field is a 2-bit field.
2277 UNREACHABLE();
2278 }
2279 }
2280 }
2281 if (((instr->Bits(7, 4) & 0xD) == 0xD) && (instr->Bit(20) == 0)) {
2282 DCHECK_EQ(rd % 2, 0);
2283 if (instr->HasH()) {
2284 // The strd instruction.
2285 int32_t value1 = get_register(rd);
2286 int32_t value2 = get_register(rd + 1);
2287 WriteDW(addr, value1, value2);
2288 } else {
2289 // The ldrd instruction.
2290 int* rn_data = ReadDW(addr);
2291 set_dw_register(rd, rn_data);
2292 }
2293 } else if (instr->HasH()) {
2294 if (instr->HasSign()) {
2295 if (instr->HasL()) {
2296 int16_t val = ReadH(addr);
2297 set_register(rd, val);
2298 } else {
2299 int16_t val = get_register(rd);
2300 WriteH(addr, val);
2301 }
2302 } else {
2303 if (instr->HasL()) {
2304 uint16_t val = ReadHU(addr);
2305 set_register(rd, val);
2306 } else {
2307 uint16_t val = get_register(rd);
2308 WriteH(addr, val);
2309 }
2310 }
2311 } else {
2312 // signed byte loads
2313 DCHECK(instr->HasSign());
2314 DCHECK(instr->HasL());
2315 int8_t val = ReadB(addr);
2316 set_register(rd, val);
2317 }
2318 return;
2319 }
2320 } else if ((type == 0) && instr->IsMiscType0()) {
2321 if ((instr->Bits(27, 23) == 2) && (instr->Bits(21, 20) == 2) &&
2322 (instr->Bits(15, 4) == 0xF00)) {
2323 // MSR
2324 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2325 DCHECK_NE(pc, rm); // UNPREDICTABLE
2326 SRegisterFieldMask sreg_and_mask =
2327 instr->BitField(22, 22) | instr->BitField(19, 16);
2328 SetSpecialRegister(sreg_and_mask, get_register(rm));
2329 } else if ((instr->Bits(27, 23) == 2) && (instr->Bits(21, 20) == 0) &&
2330 (instr->Bits(11, 0) == 0)) {
2331 // MRS
2332 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2333 DCHECK_NE(pc, rd); // UNPREDICTABLE
2334 SRegister sreg = static_cast<SRegister>(instr->BitField(22, 22));
2335 set_register(rd, GetFromSpecialRegister(sreg));
2336 } else if (instr->Bits(22, 21) == 1) {
2337 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2338 switch (instr->BitField(7, 4)) {
2339 case BX:
2340 set_pc(get_register(rm));
2341 break;
2342 case BLX: {
2343 uint32_t old_pc = get_pc();
2344 set_pc(get_register(rm));
2345 set_register(lr, old_pc + kInstrSize);
2346 break;
2347 }
2348 case BKPT:
2349 PrintF("Simulator hit BKPT. ");
2350 DebugAtNextPC();
2351 break;
2352 default:
2353 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2354 }
2355 } else if (instr->Bits(22, 21) == 3) {
2356 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2357 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2358 switch (instr->BitField(7, 4)) {
2359 case CLZ: {
2360 uint32_t bits = get_register(rm);
2361 int leading_zeros = 0;
2362 if (bits == 0) {
2363 leading_zeros = 32;
2364 } else {
2365 while ((bits & 0x80000000u) == 0) {
2366 bits <<= 1;
2367 leading_zeros++;
2368 }
2369 }
2370 set_register(rd, leading_zeros);
2371 break;
2372 }
2373 default:
2374 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2375 }
2376 } else {
2377 PrintF("%08x\n", instr->InstructionBits());
2378 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2379 }
2380 } else if ((type == 1) && instr->IsNopLikeType1()) {
2381 if (instr->BitField(7, 0) == 0) {
2382 // NOP.
2383 } else if (instr->BitField(7, 0) == 20) {
2384 // CSDB.
2385 } else {
2386 PrintF("%08x\n", instr->InstructionBits());
2387 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2388 }
2389 } else {
2390 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2391 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2392 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2393 int32_t shifter_operand = 0;
2394 bool shifter_carry_out = false;
2395 if (type == 0) {
2396 shifter_operand = GetShiftRm(instr, &shifter_carry_out);
2397 } else {
2398 DCHECK_EQ(instr->TypeValue(), 1);
2399 shifter_operand = GetImm(instr, &shifter_carry_out);
2400 }
2401 int32_t alu_out;
2402
2403 switch (instr->OpcodeField()) {
2404 case AND: {
2405 // Format(instr, "and'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2406 // Format(instr, "and'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2407 alu_out = rn_val & shifter_operand;
2408 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2409 if (instr->HasS()) {
2410 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2411 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2412 }
2413 break;
2414 }
2415
2416 case EOR: {
2417 // Format(instr, "eor'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2418 // Format(instr, "eor'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2419 alu_out = rn_val ^ shifter_operand;
2420 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2421 if (instr->HasS()) {
2422 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2423 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2424 }
2425 break;
2426 }
2427
2428 case SUB: {
2429 // Format(instr, "sub'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2430 // Format(instr, "sub'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2431 alu_out = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand);
2432 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2433 if (instr->HasS()) {
2434 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2435 SetCFlag(!BorrowFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand));
2436 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, false));
2437 }
2438 break;
2439 }
2440
2441 case RSB: {
2442 // Format(instr, "rsb'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2443 // Format(instr, "rsb'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2444 alu_out = base::SubWithWraparound(shifter_operand, rn_val);
2445 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2446 if (instr->HasS()) {
2447 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2448 SetCFlag(!BorrowFrom(shifter_operand, rn_val));
2449 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, shifter_operand, rn_val, false));
2450 }
2451 break;
2452 }
2453
2454 case ADD: {
2455 // Format(instr, "add'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2456 // Format(instr, "add'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2457 alu_out = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand);
2458 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2459 if (instr->HasS()) {
2460 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2461 SetCFlag(CarryFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand));
2462 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, true));
2463 }
2464 break;
2465 }
2466
2467 case ADC: {
2468 // Format(instr, "adc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2469 // Format(instr, "adc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2470 alu_out = base::AddWithWraparound(
2471 base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand), GetCarry());
2472 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2473 if (instr->HasS()) {
2474 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2475 SetCFlag(CarryFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand, GetCarry()));
2476 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, true));
2477 }
2478 break;
2479 }
2480
2481 case SBC: {
2482 // Format(instr, "sbc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2483 // Format(instr, "sbc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2484 alu_out = base::SubWithWraparound(
2485 base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand),
2486 (GetCarry() ? 0 : 1));
2487 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2488 if (instr->HasS()) {
2489 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2490 SetCFlag(!BorrowFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand, GetCarry()));
2491 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, false));
2492 }
2493 break;
2494 }
2495
2496 case RSC: {
2497 Format(instr, "rsc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2498 Format(instr, "rsc'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2499 break;
2500 }
2501
2502 case TST: {
2503 if (instr->HasS()) {
2504 // Format(instr, "tst'cond 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2505 // Format(instr, "tst'cond 'rn, 'imm");
2506 alu_out = rn_val & shifter_operand;
2507 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2508 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2509 } else {
2510 // Format(instr, "movw'cond 'rd, 'imm").
2511 alu_out = instr->ImmedMovwMovtValue();
2512 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2513 }
2514 break;
2515 }
2516
2517 case TEQ: {
2518 if (instr->HasS()) {
2519 // Format(instr, "teq'cond 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2520 // Format(instr, "teq'cond 'rn, 'imm");
2521 alu_out = rn_val ^ shifter_operand;
2522 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2523 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2524 } else {
2525 // Other instructions matching this pattern are handled in the
2526 // miscellaneous instructions part above.
2527 UNREACHABLE();
2528 }
2529 break;
2530 }
2531
2532 case CMP: {
2533 if (instr->HasS()) {
2534 // Format(instr, "cmp'cond 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2535 // Format(instr, "cmp'cond 'rn, 'imm");
2536 alu_out = base::SubWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand);
2537 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2538 SetCFlag(!BorrowFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand));
2539 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, false));
2540 } else {
2541 // Format(instr, "movt'cond 'rd, 'imm").
2542 alu_out =
2543 (get_register(rd) & 0xFFFF) | (instr->ImmedMovwMovtValue() << 16);
2544 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2545 }
2546 break;
2547 }
2548
2549 case CMN: {
2550 if (instr->HasS()) {
2551 // Format(instr, "cmn'cond 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2552 // Format(instr, "cmn'cond 'rn, 'imm");
2553 alu_out = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand);
2554 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2555 SetCFlag(CarryFrom(rn_val, shifter_operand));
2556 SetVFlag(OverflowFrom(alu_out, rn_val, shifter_operand, true));
2557 } else {
2558 // Other instructions matching this pattern are handled in the
2559 // miscellaneous instructions part above.
2560 UNREACHABLE();
2561 }
2562 break;
2563 }
2564
2565 case ORR: {
2566 // Format(instr, "orr'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2567 // Format(instr, "orr'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2568 alu_out = rn_val | shifter_operand;
2569 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2570 if (instr->HasS()) {
2571 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2572 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2573 }
2574 break;
2575 }
2576
2577 case MOV: {
2578 // Format(instr, "mov'cond's 'rd, 'shift_rm");
2579 // Format(instr, "mov'cond's 'rd, 'imm");
2580 alu_out = shifter_operand;
2581 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2582 if (instr->HasS()) {
2583 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2584 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2585 }
2586 break;
2587 }
2588
2589 case BIC: {
2590 // Format(instr, "bic'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'shift_rm");
2591 // Format(instr, "bic'cond's 'rd, 'rn, 'imm");
2592 alu_out = rn_val & ~shifter_operand;
2593 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2594 if (instr->HasS()) {
2595 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2596 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2597 }
2598 break;
2599 }
2600
2601 case MVN: {
2602 // Format(instr, "mvn'cond's 'rd, 'shift_rm");
2603 // Format(instr, "mvn'cond's 'rd, 'imm");
2604 alu_out = ~shifter_operand;
2605 set_register(rd, alu_out);
2606 if (instr->HasS()) {
2607 SetNZFlags(alu_out);
2608 SetCFlag(shifter_carry_out);
2609 }
2610 break;
2611 }
2612
2613 default: {
2614 UNREACHABLE();
2615 }
2616 }
2617 }
2618}
2619
2620void Simulator::DecodeType2(Instruction* instr) {
2621 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2622 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2623 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2624 int32_t im_val = instr->Offset12Value();
2625 int32_t addr = 0;
2626 switch (instr->PUField()) {
2627 case da_x: {
2628 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn], #-'off12");
2629 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2630 addr = rn_val;
2631 rn_val -= im_val;
2632 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2633 break;
2634 }
2635 case ia_x: {
2636 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn], #+'off12");
2637 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2638 addr = rn_val;
2639 rn_val += im_val;
2640 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2641 break;
2642 }
2643 case db_x: {
2644 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn, #-'off12]'w");
2645 rn_val -= im_val;
2646 addr = rn_val;
2647 if (instr->HasW()) {
2648 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2649 }
2650 break;
2651 }
2652 case ib_x: {
2653 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn, #+'off12]'w");
2654 rn_val += im_val;
2655 addr = rn_val;
2656 if (instr->HasW()) {
2657 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2658 }
2659 break;
2660 }
2661 default: {
2662 UNREACHABLE();
2663 }
2664 }
2665 if (instr->HasB()) {
2666 if (instr->HasL()) {
2667 uint8_t val = ReadBU(addr);
2668 set_register(rd, val);
2669 } else {
2670 uint8_t val = get_register(rd);
2671 WriteB(addr, val);
2672 }
2673 } else {
2674 if (instr->HasL()) {
2675 set_register(rd, ReadW(addr));
2676 } else {
2677 WriteW(addr, get_register(rd));
2678 }
2679 }
2680}
2681
2682void Simulator::DecodeType3(Instruction* instr) {
2683 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2684 int rn = instr->RnValue();
2685 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2686 bool shifter_carry_out = false;
2687 int32_t shifter_operand = GetShiftRm(instr, &shifter_carry_out);
2688 int32_t addr = 0;
2689 switch (instr->PUField()) {
2690 case da_x: {
2691 DCHECK(!instr->HasW());
2692 Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn], -'shift_rm");
2693 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2694 }
2695 case ia_x: {
2696 if (instr->Bit(4) == 0) {
2697 // Memop.
2698 } else {
2699 if (instr->Bit(5) == 0) {
2700 switch (instr->Bits(22, 21)) {
2701 case 0:
2702 if (instr->Bit(20) == 0) {
2703 if (instr->Bit(6) == 0) {
2704 // Pkhbt.
2705 uint32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2706 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2707 int32_t shift = instr->Bits(11, 7);
2708 rm_val <<= shift;
2709 set_register(rd, (rn_val & 0xFFFF) | (rm_val & 0xFFFF0000U));
2710 } else {
2711 // Pkhtb.
2712 uint32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2713 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2714 int32_t shift = instr->Bits(11, 7);
2715 if (shift == 0) {
2716 shift = 32;
2717 }
2718 rm_val >>= shift;
2719 set_register(rd, (rn_val & 0xFFFF0000U) | (rm_val & 0xFFFF));
2720 }
2721 } else {
2722 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2723 }
2724 break;
2725 case 1:
2726 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2727 case 2:
2728 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2729 case 3: {
2730 // Usat.
2731 int32_t sat_pos = instr->Bits(20, 16);
2732 int32_t sat_val = (1 << sat_pos) - 1;
2733 int32_t shift = instr->Bits(11, 7);
2734 int32_t shift_type = instr->Bit(6);
2735 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2736 if (shift_type == 0) { // LSL
2737 rm_val <<= shift;
2738 } else { // ASR
2739 rm_val >>= shift;
2740 }
2741 // If saturation occurs, the Q flag should be set in the CPSR.
2742 // There is no Q flag yet, and no instruction (MRS) to read the
2743 // CPSR directly.
2744 if (rm_val > sat_val) {
2745 rm_val = sat_val;
2746 } else if (rm_val < 0) {
2747 rm_val = 0;
2748 }
2749 set_register(rd, rm_val);
2750 break;
2751 }
2752 }
2753 } else {
2754 switch (instr->Bits(22, 21)) {
2755 case 0:
2756 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2757 case 1:
2758 if (instr->Bits(9, 6) == 1) {
2759 if (instr->Bit(20) == 0) {
2760 if (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0xF) {
2761 // Sxtb.
2762 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2763 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2764 switch (rotate) {
2765 case 0:
2766 break;
2767 case 1:
2768 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2769 break;
2770 case 2:
2771 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2772 break;
2773 case 3:
2774 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2775 break;
2776 }
2777 set_register(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rm_val));
2778 } else {
2779 // Sxtab.
2780 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2781 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2782 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2783 switch (rotate) {
2784 case 0:
2785 break;
2786 case 1:
2787 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2788 break;
2789 case 2:
2790 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2791 break;
2792 case 3:
2793 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2794 break;
2795 }
2796 set_register(rd, rn_val + static_cast<int8_t>(rm_val));
2797 }
2798 } else {
2799 if (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0xF) {
2800 // Sxth.
2801 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2802 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2803 switch (rotate) {
2804 case 0:
2805 break;
2806 case 1:
2807 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2808 break;
2809 case 2:
2810 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2811 break;
2812 case 3:
2813 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2814 break;
2815 }
2816 set_register(rd, static_cast<int16_t>(rm_val));
2817 } else {
2818 // Sxtah.
2819 int32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2820 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2821 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2822 switch (rotate) {
2823 case 0:
2824 break;
2825 case 1:
2826 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2827 break;
2828 case 2:
2829 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2830 break;
2831 case 3:
2832 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2833 break;
2834 }
2835 set_register(rd, rn_val + static_cast<int16_t>(rm_val));
2836 }
2837 }
2838 } else if (instr->Bits(27, 16) == 0x6BF &&
2839 instr->Bits(11, 4) == 0xF3) {
2840 // Rev.
2841 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2842 set_register(rd, ByteReverse(rm_val));
2843 } else {
2844 UNREACHABLE();
2845 }
2846 break;
2847 case 2:
2848 if ((instr->Bit(20) == 0) && (instr->Bits(9, 6) == 1)) {
2849 if (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0xF) {
2850 // Uxtb16.
2851 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2852 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2853 switch (rotate) {
2854 case 0:
2855 break;
2856 case 1:
2857 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2858 break;
2859 case 2:
2860 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2861 break;
2862 case 3:
2863 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2864 break;
2865 }
2866 set_register(rd, (rm_val & 0xFF) | (rm_val & 0xFF0000));
2867 } else {
2868 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2869 }
2870 } else {
2871 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2872 }
2873 break;
2874 case 3:
2875 if ((instr->Bits(9, 6) == 1)) {
2876 if (instr->Bit(20) == 0) {
2877 if (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0xF) {
2878 // Uxtb.
2879 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2880 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2881 switch (rotate) {
2882 case 0:
2883 break;
2884 case 1:
2885 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2886 break;
2887 case 2:
2888 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2889 break;
2890 case 3:
2891 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2892 break;
2893 }
2894 set_register(rd, (rm_val & 0xFF));
2895 } else {
2896 // Uxtab.
2897 uint32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2898 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2899 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2900 switch (rotate) {
2901 case 0:
2902 break;
2903 case 1:
2904 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2905 break;
2906 case 2:
2907 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2908 break;
2909 case 3:
2910 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2911 break;
2912 }
2913 set_register(rd, rn_val + (rm_val & 0xFF));
2914 }
2915 } else {
2916 if (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0xF) {
2917 // Uxth.
2918 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2919 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2920 switch (rotate) {
2921 case 0:
2922 break;
2923 case 1:
2924 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2925 break;
2926 case 2:
2927 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2928 break;
2929 case 3:
2930 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2931 break;
2932 }
2933 set_register(rd, (rm_val & 0xFFFF));
2934 } else {
2935 // Uxtah.
2936 uint32_t rn_val = get_register(rn);
2937 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2938 int32_t rotate = instr->Bits(11, 10);
2939 switch (rotate) {
2940 case 0:
2941 break;
2942 case 1:
2943 rm_val = (rm_val >> 8) | (rm_val << 24);
2944 break;
2945 case 2:
2946 rm_val = (rm_val >> 16) | (rm_val << 16);
2947 break;
2948 case 3:
2949 rm_val = (rm_val >> 24) | (rm_val << 8);
2950 break;
2951 }
2952 set_register(rd, rn_val + (rm_val & 0xFFFF));
2953 }
2954 }
2955 } else {
2956 // PU == 0b01, BW == 0b11, Bits(9, 6) != 0b0001
2957 if ((instr->Bits(20, 16) == 0x1F) &&
2958 (instr->Bits(11, 4) == 0xF3)) {
2959 // Rbit.
2960 uint32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
2961 set_register(rd, base::bits::ReverseBits(rm_val));
2962 } else {
2963 UNIMPLEMENTED();
2964 }
2965 }
2966 break;
2967 }
2968 }
2969 return;
2970 }
2971 break;
2972 }
2973 case db_x: {
2974 if (instr->Bits(22, 20) == 0x5) {
2975 if (instr->Bits(7, 4) == 0x1) {
2976 int rm = instr->RmValue();
2977 int32_t rm_val = get_register(rm);
2978 int rs = instr->RsValue();
2979 int32_t rs_val = get_register(rs);
2980 if (instr->Bits(15, 12) == 0xF) {
2981 // SMMUL (in V8 notation matching ARM ISA format)
2982 // Format(instr, "smmul'cond 'rn, 'rm, 'rs");
2983 rn_val = base::bits::SignedMulHigh32(rm_val, rs_val);
2984 } else {
2985 // SMMLA (in V8 notation matching ARM ISA format)
2986 // Format(instr, "smmla'cond 'rn, 'rm, 'rs, 'rd");
2987 int rd = instr->RdValue();
2988 int32_t rd_val = get_register(rd);
2989 rn_val = base::bits::SignedMulHighAndAdd32(rm_val, rs_val, rd_val);
2990 }
2991 set_register(rn, rn_val);
2992 return;
2993 }
2994 }
2995 if (instr->Bits(5, 4) == 0x1) {
2996 if ((instr->Bit(22) == 0x0) && (instr->Bit(20) == 0x1)) {
2997 // (s/u)div (in V8 notation matching ARM ISA format) rn = rm/rs
2998 // Format(instr, "'(s/u)div'cond'b 'rn, 'rm, 'rs);
2999 int rm = instr->RmValue();
3000 int32_t rm_val = get_register(rm);
3001 int rs = instr->RsValue();
3002 int32_t rs_val = get_register(rs);
3003 int32_t ret_val = 0;
3004 // udiv
3005 if (instr->Bit(21) == 0x1) {
3006 ret_val = base::bit_cast<int32_t>(
3007 base::bits::UnsignedDiv32(base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(rm_val),
3008 base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(rs_val)));
3009 } else {
3010 ret_val = base::bits::SignedDiv32(rm_val, rs_val);
3011 }
3012 set_register(rn, ret_val);
3013 return;
3014 }
3015 }
3016 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn, -'shift_rm]'w");
3017 addr = rn_val - shifter_operand;
3018 if (instr->HasW()) {
3019 set_register(rn, addr);
3020 }
3021 break;
3022 }
3023 case ib_x: {
3024 if (instr->HasW() && (instr->Bits(6, 4) == 0x5)) {
3025 uint32_t widthminus1 = static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->Bits(20, 16));
3026 uint32_t lsbit = static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->Bits(11, 7));
3027 uint32_t msbit = widthminus1 + lsbit;
3028 if (msbit <= 31) {
3029 if (instr->Bit(22)) {
3030 // ubfx - unsigned bitfield extract.
3031 uint32_t rm_val =
3032 static_cast<uint32_t>(get_register(instr->RmValue()));
3033 uint32_t extr_val = rm_val << (31 - msbit);
3034 extr_val = extr_val >> (31 - widthminus1);
3035 set_register(instr->RdValue(), extr_val);
3036 } else {
3037 // sbfx - signed bitfield extract.
3038 int32_t rm_val = get_register(instr->RmValue());
3039 int32_t extr_val = static_cast<uint32_t>(rm_val) << (31 - msbit);
3040 extr_val = extr_val >> (31 - widthminus1);
3041 set_register(instr->RdValue(), extr_val);
3042 }
3043 } else {
3044 UNREACHABLE();
3045 }
3046 return;
3047 } else if (!instr->HasW() && (instr->Bits(6, 4) == 0x1)) {
3048 uint32_t lsbit = static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->Bits(11, 7));
3049 uint32_t msbit = static_cast<uint32_t>(instr->Bits(20, 16));
3050 if (msbit >= lsbit) {
3051 // bfc or bfi - bitfield clear/insert.
3052 uint32_t rd_val =
3053 static_cast<uint32_t>(get_register(instr->RdValue()));
3054 uint32_t bitcount = msbit - lsbit + 1;
3055 uint32_t mask = 0xFFFFFFFFu >> (32 - bitcount);
3056 rd_val &= ~(mask << lsbit);
3057 if (instr->RmValue() != 15) {
3058 // bfi - bitfield insert.
3059 uint32_t rm_val =
3060 static_cast<uint32_t>(get_register(instr->RmValue()));
3061 rm_val &= mask;
3062 rd_val |= rm_val << lsbit;
3063 }
3064 set_register(instr->RdValue(), rd_val);
3065 } else {
3066 UNREACHABLE();
3067 }
3068 return;
3069 } else {
3070 // Format(instr, "'memop'cond'b 'rd, ['rn, +'shift_rm]'w");
3071 addr = base::AddWithWraparound(rn_val, shifter_operand);
3072 if (instr->HasW()) {
3073 set_register(rn, addr);
3074 }
3075 }
3076 break;
3077 }
3078 default: {
3079 UNREACHABLE();
3080 }
3081 }
3082 if (instr->HasB()) {
3083 if (instr->HasL()) {
3084 uint8_t byte = ReadB(addr);
3085 set_register(rd, byte);
3086 } else {
3087 uint8_t byte = get_register(rd);
3088 WriteB(addr, byte);
3089 }
3090 } else {
3091 if (instr->HasL()) {
3092 set_register(rd, ReadW(addr));
3093 } else {
3094 WriteW(addr, get_register(rd));
3095 }
3096 }
3097}

3144// void Simulator::DecodeTypeVFP(Instruction* instr)
3145// The Following ARMv7 VFPv instructions are currently supported.
3146// vmov :Sn = Rt
3147// vmov :Rt = Sn
3148// vcvt: Dd = Sm
3149// vcvt: Sd = Dm
3150// vcvt.f64.s32 Dd, Dd, #<fbits>
3151// Dd = vabs(Dm)
3152// Sd = vabs(Sm)
3153// Dd = vneg(Dm)
3154// Sd = vneg(Sm)
3155// Dd = vadd(Dn, Dm)
3156// Sd = vadd(Sn, Sm)
3157// Dd = vsub(Dn, Dm)
3158// Sd = vsub(Sn, Sm)
3159// Dd = vmul(Dn, Dm)
3160// Sd = vmul(Sn, Sm)
3161// Dd = vdiv(Dn, Dm)
3162// Sd = vdiv(Sn, Sm)
3163// vcmp(Dd, Dm)
3164// vcmp(Sd, Sm)
3165// Dd = vsqrt(Dm)
3166// Sd = vsqrt(Sm)
3167// vmrs
3168// vdup.size Qd, Rt.
3169void Simulator::DecodeTypeVFP(Instruction* instr) {
3170 DCHECK((instr->TypeValue() == 7) && (instr->Bit(24) == 0x0));
3171 DCHECK_EQ(instr->Bits(11, 9), 0x5);
3172 // Obtain single precision register codes.
3173 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3174 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3175 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3176 // Obtain double precision register codes.
3177 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3178 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3179 int vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3180
3181 if (instr->Bit(4) == 0) {
3182 if (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x7) {
3183 // Other data processing instructions
3184 if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x0) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x1)) {
3185 // vmov register to register.
3186 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3187 uint32_t data[2];
3188 get_d_register(vm, data);
3189 set_d_register(vd, data);
3190 } else {
3191 set_s_register(d, get_s_register(m));
3192 }
3193 } else if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x0) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3)) {
3194 // vabs
3195 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3196 Float64 dm = get_double_from_d_register(vm);
3197 constexpr uint64_t kSignBit64 = uint64_t{1} << 63;
3198 Float64 dd = Float64::FromBits(dm.get_bits() & ~kSignBit64);
3199 dd = canonicalizeNaN(dd);
3200 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd);
3201 } else {
3202 Float32 sm = get_float_from_s_register(m);
3203 constexpr uint32_t kSignBit32 = uint32_t{1} << 31;
3204 Float32 sd = Float32::FromBits(sm.get_bits() & ~kSignBit32);
3205 sd = canonicalizeNaN(sd);
3206 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd);
3207 }
3208 } else if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x1) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x1)) {
3209 // vneg
3210 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3211 Float64 dm = get_double_from_d_register(vm);
3212 constexpr uint64_t kSignBit64 = uint64_t{1} << 63;
3213 Float64 dd = Float64::FromBits(dm.get_bits() ^ kSignBit64);
3214 dd = canonicalizeNaN(dd);
3215 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd);
3216 } else {
3217 Float32 sm = get_float_from_s_register(m);
3218 constexpr uint32_t kSignBit32 = uint32_t{1} << 31;
3219 Float32 sd = Float32::FromBits(sm.get_bits() ^ kSignBit32);
3220 sd = canonicalizeNaN(sd);
3221 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd);
3222 }
3223 } else if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x7) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3)) {
3224 DecodeVCVTBetweenDoubleAndSingle(instr);
3225 } else if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x8) && (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) {
3226 DecodeVCVTBetweenFloatingPointAndInteger(instr);
3227 } else if ((instr->Opc2Value() == 0xA) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3) &&
3228 (instr->Bit(8) == 1)) {
3229 // vcvt.f64.s32 Dd, Dd, #<fbits>
3230 int fraction_bits = 32 - ((instr->Bits(3, 0) << 1) | instr->Bit(5));
3231 int fixed_value = get_sinteger_from_s_register(vd * 2);
3232 double divide = 1 << fraction_bits;
3233 set_d_register_from_double(vd, fixed_value / divide);
3234 } else if (((instr->Opc2Value() >> 1) == 0x6) &&
3235 (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) {
3236 DecodeVCVTBetweenFloatingPointAndInteger(instr);
3237 } else if (((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x4) || (instr->Opc2Value() == 0x5)) &&
3238 (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) {
3239 DecodeVCMP(instr);
3240 } else if (((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x1)) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3)) {
3241 // vsqrt
3242 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3243 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3244 double dd_value = std::sqrt(dm_value);
3245 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3246 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3247 } else {
3248 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3249 float sd_value = std::sqrt(sm_value);
3250 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3251 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3252 }
3253 } else if (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x0) {
3254 // vmov immediate.
3255 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3256 set_d_register_from_double(vd, instr->DoubleImmedVmov());
3257 } else {
3258 // Cast double to float.
3259 float value = instr->DoubleImmedVmov().get_scalar();
3260 set_s_register_from_float(d, value);
3261 }
3262 } else if (((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x6)) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3)) {
3263 // vrintz - truncate
3264 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3265 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3266 double dd_value = trunc(dm_value);
3267 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3268 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3269 } else {
3270 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3271 float sd_value = truncf(sm_value);
3272 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3273 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3274 }
3275 } else {
3276 UNREACHABLE(); // Not used by V8.
3277 }
3278 } else if (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x3) {
3279 if (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1) {
3280 // vsub
3281 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3282 double dn_value = get_double_from_d_register(vn).get_scalar();
3283 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3284 double dd_value = dn_value - dm_value;
3285 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3286 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3287 } else {
3288 float sn_value = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
3289 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3290 float sd_value = sn_value - sm_value;
3291 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3292 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3293 }
3294 } else {
3295 // vadd
3296 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3297 double dn_value = get_double_from_d_register(vn).get_scalar();
3298 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3299 double dd_value = dn_value + dm_value;
3300 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3301 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3302 } else {
3303 float sn_value = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
3304 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3305 float sd_value = sn_value + sm_value;
3306 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3307 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3308 }
3309 }
3310 } else if ((instr->Opc1Value() == 0x2) && !(instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) {
3311 // vmul
3312 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3313 double dn_value = get_double_from_d_register(vn).get_scalar();
3314 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3315 double dd_value = dn_value * dm_value;
3316 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3317 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3318 } else {
3319 float sn_value = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
3320 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3321 float sd_value = sn_value * sm_value;
3322 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3323 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3324 }
3325 } else if ((instr->Opc1Value() == 0x0)) {
3326 // vmla, vmls
3327 const bool is_vmls = (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1);
3328 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3329 const double dd_val = get_double_from_d_register(vd).get_scalar();
3330 const double dn_val = get_double_from_d_register(vn).get_scalar();
3331 const double dm_val = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3332
3333 // Note: we do the mul and add/sub in separate steps to avoid getting a
3334 // result with too high precision.
3335 const double res = dn_val * dm_val;
3336 set_d_register_from_double(vd, res);
3337 if (is_vmls) {
3338 set_d_register_from_double(vd, canonicalizeNaN(dd_val - res));
3339 } else {
3340 set_d_register_from_double(vd, canonicalizeNaN(dd_val + res));
3341 }
3342 } else {
3343 const float sd_val = get_float_from_s_register(d).get_scalar();
3344 const float sn_val = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
3345 const float sm_val = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3346
3347 // Note: we do the mul and add/sub in separate steps to avoid getting a
3348 // result with too high precision.
3349 const float res = sn_val * sm_val;
3350 set_s_register_from_float(d, res);
3351 if (is_vmls) {
3352 set_s_register_from_float(d, canonicalizeNaN(sd_val - res));
3353 } else {
3354 set_s_register_from_float(d, canonicalizeNaN(sd_val + res));
3355 }
3356 }
3357 } else if ((instr->Opc1Value() == 0x4) && !(instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) {
3358 // vdiv
3359 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3360 double dn_value = get_double_from_d_register(vn).get_scalar();
3361 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
3362 double dd_value = base::Divide(dn_value, dm_value);
3363 div_zero_vfp_flag_ = (dm_value == 0);
3364 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
3365 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
3366 } else {
3367 float sn_value = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
3368 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3369 float sd_value = base::Divide(sn_value, sm_value);
3370 div_zero_vfp_flag_ = (sm_value == 0);
3371 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
3372 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
3373 }
3374 } else {
3375 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3376 }
3377 } else {
3378 if ((instr->VCValue() == 0x0) && (instr->VAValue() == 0x0)) {
3379 DecodeVMOVBetweenCoreAndSinglePrecisionRegisters(instr);
3380 } else if ((instr->VLValue() == 0x0) && (instr->VCValue() == 0x1)) {
3381 if (instr->Bit(23) == 0) {
3382 // vmov (ARM core register to scalar)
3383 int vd = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3384 int rt = instr->RtValue();
3385 int opc1_opc2 = (instr->Bits(22, 21) << 2) | instr->Bits(6, 5);
3386 if ((opc1_opc2 & 0xB) == 0) {
3387 // NeonS32/NeonU32
3388 uint32_t data[2];
3389 get_d_register(vd, data);
3390 data[instr->Bit(21)] = get_register(rt);
3391 set_d_register(vd, data);
3392 } else {
3393 uint64_t data;
3394 get_d_register(vd, &data);
3395 uint64_t rt_value = get_register(rt);
3396 if ((opc1_opc2 & 0x8) != 0) {
3397 // NeonS8 / NeonU8
3398 int i = opc1_opc2 & 0x7;
3399 int shift = i * kBitsPerByte;
3400 const uint64_t mask = 0xFF;
3401 data &= ~(mask << shift);
3402 data |= (rt_value & mask) << shift;
3403 set_d_register(vd, &data);
3404 } else if ((opc1_opc2 & 0x1) != 0) {
3405 // NeonS16 / NeonU16
3406 int i = (opc1_opc2 >> 1) & 0x3;
3407 int shift = i * kBitsPerByte * kShortSize;
3408 const uint64_t mask = 0xFFFF;
3409 data &= ~(mask << shift);
3410 data |= (rt_value & mask) << shift;
3411 set_d_register(vd, &data);
3412 } else {
3413 UNREACHABLE(); // Not used by V8.
3414 }
3415 }
3416 } else {
3417 // vdup.size Qd, Rt.
3418 NeonSize size = Neon32;
3419 if (instr->Bit(5) != 0)
3420 size = Neon16;
3421 else if (instr->Bit(22) != 0)
3422 size = Neon8;
3423 int vd = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
3424 int rt = instr->RtValue();
3425 uint32_t rt_value = get_register(rt);
3426 uint32_t q_data[4];
3427 switch (size) {
3428 case Neon8: {
3429 rt_value &= 0xFF;
3430 uint8_t* dst = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(q_data);
3431 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
3432 dst[i] = rt_value;
3433 }
3434 break;
3435 }
3436 case Neon16: {
3437 // Perform pairwise op.
3438 rt_value &= 0xFFFFu;
3439 uint32_t rt_rt = (rt_value << 16) | (rt_value & 0xFFFFu);
3440 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3441 q_data[i] = rt_rt;
3442 }
3443 break;
3444 }
3445 case Neon32: {
3446 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
3447 q_data[i] = rt_value;
3448 }
3449 break;
3450 }
3451 default:
3452 UNREACHABLE();
3453 }
3454 set_neon_register(vd, q_data);
3455 }
3456 } else if ((instr->VLValue() == 0x1) && (instr->VCValue() == 0x1)) {
3457 // vmov (scalar to ARM core register)
3458 int vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3459 int rt = instr->RtValue();
3460 int opc1_opc2 = (instr->Bits(22, 21) << 2) | instr->Bits(6, 5);
3461 uint64_t data;
3462 get_d_register(vn, &data);
3463 if ((opc1_opc2 & 0xB) == 0) {
3464 // NeonS32 / NeonU32
3465 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bit(23));
3466 int32_t int_data[2];
3467 memcpy(int_data, &data, sizeof(int_data));
3468 set_register(rt, int_data[instr->Bit(21)]);
3469 } else {
3470 uint64_t data;
3471 get_d_register(vn, &data);
3472 bool u = instr->Bit(23) != 0;
3473 if ((opc1_opc2 & 0x8) != 0) {
3474 // NeonS8 / NeonU8
3475 int i = opc1_opc2 & 0x7;
3476 int shift = i * kBitsPerByte;
3477 uint32_t scalar = (data >> shift) & 0xFFu;
3478 if (!u && (scalar & 0x80) != 0) scalar |= 0xFFFFFF00;
3479 set_register(rt, scalar);
3480 } else if ((opc1_opc2 & 0x1) != 0) {
3481 // NeonS16 / NeonU16
3482 int i = (opc1_opc2 >> 1) & 0x3;
3483 int shift = i * kBitsPerByte * kShortSize;
3484 uint32_t scalar = (data >> shift) & 0xFFFFu;
3485 if (!u && (scalar & 0x8000) != 0) scalar |= 0xFFFF0000;
3486 set_register(rt, scalar);
3487 } else {
3488 UNREACHABLE(); // Not used by V8.
3489 }
3490 }
3491 } else if ((instr->VLValue() == 0x1) && (instr->VCValue() == 0x0) &&
3492 (instr->VAValue() == 0x7) && (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0x1)) {
3493 // vmrs
3494 uint32_t rt = instr->RtValue();
3495 if (rt == 0xF) {
3496 Copy_FPSCR_to_APSR();
3497 } else {
3498 // Emulate FPSCR from the Simulator flags.
3499 uint32_t fpscr = (n_flag_FPSCR_ << 31) | (z_flag_FPSCR_ << 30) |
3500 (c_flag_FPSCR_ << 29) | (v_flag_FPSCR_ << 28) |
3501 (FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ << 25) |
3502 (inexact_vfp_flag_ << 4) | (underflow_vfp_flag_ << 3) |
3503 (overflow_vfp_flag_ << 2) | (div_zero_vfp_flag_ << 1) |
3504 (inv_op_vfp_flag_ << 0) | (FPSCR_rounding_mode_);
3505 set_register(rt, fpscr);
3506 }
3507 } else if ((instr->VLValue() == 0x0) && (instr->VCValue() == 0x0) &&
3508 (instr->VAValue() == 0x7) && (instr->Bits(19, 16) == 0x1)) {
3509 // vmsr
3510 uint32_t rt = instr->RtValue();
3511 if (rt == pc) {
3512 UNREACHABLE();
3513 } else {
3514 uint32_t rt_value = get_register(rt);
3515 n_flag_FPSCR_ = (rt_value >> 31) & 1;
3516 z_flag_FPSCR_ = (rt_value >> 30) & 1;
3517 c_flag_FPSCR_ = (rt_value >> 29) & 1;
3518 v_flag_FPSCR_ = (rt_value >> 28) & 1;
3519 FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ = (rt_value >> 25) & 1;
3520 inexact_vfp_flag_ = (rt_value >> 4) & 1;
3521 underflow_vfp_flag_ = (rt_value >> 3) & 1;
3522 overflow_vfp_flag_ = (rt_value >> 2) & 1;
3523 div_zero_vfp_flag_ = (rt_value >> 1) & 1;
3524 inv_op_vfp_flag_ = (rt_value >> 0) & 1;
3525 FPSCR_rounding_mode_ =
3526 static_cast<VFPRoundingMode>((rt_value)&kVFPRoundingModeMask);
3527 }
3528 } else {
3529 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3530 }
3531 }
3532}

3534void Simulator::DecodeTypeCP15(Instruction* instr) {
3535 DCHECK((instr->TypeValue() == 7) && (instr->Bit(24) == 0x0));
3536 DCHECK_EQ(instr->CoprocessorValue(), 15);
3537
3538 if (instr->Bit(4) == 1) {
3539 // mcr
3540 int crn = instr->Bits(19, 16);
3541 int crm = instr->Bits(3, 0);
3542 int opc1 = instr->Bits(23, 21);
3543 int opc2 = instr->Bits(7, 5);
3544 if ((opc1 == 0) && (crn == 7)) {
3545 // ARMv6 memory barrier operations.
3546 // Details available in ARM DDI 0406C.b, B3-1750.
3547 if (((crm == 10) && (opc2 == 5)) || // CP15DMB
3548 ((crm == 10) && (opc2 == 4)) || // CP15DSB
3549 ((crm == 5) && (opc2 == 4))) { // CP15ISB
3550 // These are ignored by the simulator for now.
3551 } else {
3552 UNIMPLEMENTED();
3553 }
3554 }
3555 } else {
3556 UNIMPLEMENTED();
3557 }
3558}

3560void Simulator::DecodeVMOVBetweenCoreAndSinglePrecisionRegisters(
3561 Instruction* instr) {
3562 DCHECK((instr->Bit(4) == 1) && (instr->VCValue() == 0x0) &&
3563 (instr->VAValue() == 0x0));
3564
3565 int t = instr->RtValue();
3566 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3567 bool to_arm_register = (instr->VLValue() == 0x1);
3568
3569 if (to_arm_register) {
3570 int32_t int_value = get_sinteger_from_s_register(n);
3571 set_register(t, int_value);
3572 } else {
3573 int32_t rs_val = get_register(t);
3574 set_s_register_from_sinteger(n, rs_val);
3575 }

3577
3578void Simulator::DecodeVCMP(Instruction* instr) {
3579 DCHECK((instr->Bit(4) == 0) && (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x7));
3580 DCHECK(((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x4) || (instr->Opc2Value() == 0x5)) &&
3581 (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1));
3582 // Comparison.
3583
3584 VFPRegPrecision precision = kSinglePrecision;
3585 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
3586 precision = kDoublePrecision;
3587 }
3588
3589 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(precision);
3590 int m = 0;
3591 if (instr->Opc2Value() == 0x4) {
3592 m = instr->VFPMRegValue(precision);
3593 }
3594
3595 if (precision == kDoublePrecision) {
3596 double dd_value = get_double_from_d_register(d).get_scalar();
3597 double dm_value = 0.0;
3598 if (instr->Opc2Value() == 0x4) {
3599 dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(m).get_scalar();
3600 }
3601
3602 // Raise exceptions for quiet NaNs if necessary.
3603 if (instr->Bit(7) == 1) {
3604 if (std::isnan(dd_value)) {
3605 inv_op_vfp_flag_ = true;
3606 }
3607 }
3608
3609 Compute_FPSCR_Flags(dd_value, dm_value);
3610 } else {
3611 float sd_value = get_float_from_s_register(d).get_scalar();
3612 float sm_value = 0.0;
3613 if (instr->Opc2Value() == 0x4) {
3614 sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
3615 }
3616
3617 // Raise exceptions for quiet NaNs if necessary.
3618 if (instr->Bit(7) == 1) {
3619 if (std::isnan(sd_value)) {
3620 inv_op_vfp_flag_ = true;
3621 }
3622 }
3623
3624 Compute_FPSCR_Flags(sd_value, sm_value);
3625 }
3626}
3627
3628void Simulator::DecodeVCVTBetweenDoubleAndSingle(Instruction* instr) {
3629 DCHECK((instr->Bit(4) == 0) && (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x7));
3630 DCHECK((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x7) && (instr->Opc3Value() == 0x3));
3631
3632 VFPRegPrecision dst_precision = kDoublePrecision;
3633 VFPRegPrecision src_precision = kSinglePrecision;
3634 if (instr->SzValue() == 1) {
3635 dst_precision = kSinglePrecision;
3636 src_precision = kDoublePrecision;
3637 }
3638
3639 int dst = instr->VFPDRegValue(dst_precision);
3640 int src = instr->VFPMRegValue(src_precision);
3641
3642 if (dst_precision == kSinglePrecision) {
3643 double val = get_double_from_d_register(src).get_scalar();
3644 set_s_register_from_float(dst, static_cast<float>(val));
3645 } else {
3646 float val = get_float_from_s_register(src).get_scalar();
3647 set_d_register_from_double(dst, static_cast<double>(val));
3648 }
3649}
3650
3651bool get_inv_op_vfp_flag(VFPRoundingMode mode, double val, bool unsigned_) {
3652 DCHECK((mode == RN) || (mode == RM) || (mode == RZ));
3653 double max_uint = static_cast<double>(0xFFFFFFFFu);
3654 double max_int = static_cast<double>(kMaxInt);
3655 double min_int = static_cast<double>(kMinInt);
3656
3657 // Check for NaN.
3658 if (val != val) {
3659 return true;
3660 }
3661
3662 // Check for overflow. This code works because 32bit integers can be
3663 // exactly represented by ieee-754 64bit floating-point values.
3664 switch (mode) {
3665 case RN:
3666 return unsigned_ ? (val >= (max_uint + 0.5)) || (val < -0.5)
3667 : (val >= (max_int + 0.5)) || (val < (min_int - 0.5));
3668
3669 case RM:
3670 return unsigned_ ? (val >= (max_uint + 1.0)) || (val < 0)
3671 : (val >= (max_int + 1.0)) || (val < min_int);
3672
3673 case RZ:
3674 return unsigned_ ? (val >= (max_uint + 1.0)) || (val <= -1)
3675 : (val >= (max_int + 1.0)) || (val <= (min_int - 1.0));
3676 default:
3677 UNREACHABLE();
3678 }
3679}
3680
3681// We call this function only if we had a vfp invalid exception.
3682// It returns the correct saturated value.
3683int VFPConversionSaturate(double val, bool unsigned_res) {
3684 if (val != val) {
3685 return 0;
3686 } else {
3687 if (unsigned_res) {
3688 return (val < 0) ? 0 : 0xFFFFFFFFu;
3689 } else {
3690 return (val < 0) ? kMinInt : kMaxInt;
3691 }
3692 }
3693}
3694
3695int32_t Simulator::ConvertDoubleToInt(double val, bool unsigned_integer,
3696 VFPRoundingMode mode) {
3697 int32_t result;
3698 if (unsigned_integer) {
3699 // The FastD2UI helper does not have the rounding behavior we want here
3700 // (it doesn't guarantee any particular rounding, and it doesn't check
3701 // for or handle overflow), so do the conversion by hand.
3702 using limits = std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>;
3703 if (val > limits::max()) {
3704 result = limits::max();
3705 } else if (!(val >= 0)) { // Negation to catch NaNs.
3706 result = 0;
3707 } else {
3708 result = static_cast<uint32_t>(val);
3709 }
3710 } else {
3711 result = FastD2IChecked(val);
3712 }
3713
3714 inv_op_vfp_flag_ = get_inv_op_vfp_flag(mode, val, unsigned_integer);
3715
3716 double abs_diff = unsigned_integer
3717 ? std::fabs(val - static_cast<uint32_t>(result))
3718 : std::fabs(val - result);
3719
3720 inexact_vfp_flag_ = (abs_diff != 0);
3721
3722 if (inv_op_vfp_flag_) {
3723 result = VFPConversionSaturate(val, unsigned_integer);
3724 } else {
3725 switch (mode) {
3726 case RN: {
3727 int val_sign = (val > 0) ? 1 : -1;
3728 if (abs_diff > 0.5) {
3729 result += val_sign;
3730 } else if (abs_diff == 0.5) {
3731 // Round to even if exactly halfway.
3732 result = ((result % 2) == 0)
3733 ? result
3734 : base::AddWithWraparound(result, val_sign);
3735 }
3736 break;
3737 }
3738
3739 case RM:
3740 result = result > val ? result - 1 : result;
3741 break;
3742
3743 case RZ:
3744 // Nothing to do.
3745 break;
3746
3747 default:
3748 UNREACHABLE();
3749 }
3750 }
3751 return result;
3752}
3753
3754void Simulator::DecodeVCVTBetweenFloatingPointAndInteger(Instruction* instr) {
3755 DCHECK((instr->Bit(4) == 0) && (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x7) &&
3756 (instr->Bits(27, 23) == 0x1D));
3757 DCHECK(((instr->Opc2Value() == 0x8) && (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)) ||
3758 (((instr->Opc2Value() >> 1) == 0x6) && (instr->Opc3Value() & 0x1)));
3759
3760 // Conversion between floating-point and integer.
3761 bool to_integer = (instr->Bit(18) == 1);
3762
3763 VFPRegPrecision src_precision =
3764 (instr->SzValue() == 1) ? kDoublePrecision : kSinglePrecision;
3765
3766 if (to_integer) {
3767 // We are playing with code close to the C++ standard's limits below,
3768 // hence the very simple code and heavy checks.
3769 //
3770 // Note:
3771 // C++ defines default type casting from floating point to integer as
3772 // (close to) rounding toward zero ("fractional part discarded").
3773
3774 int dst = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3775 int src = instr->VFPMRegValue(src_precision);
3776
3777 // Bit 7 in vcvt instructions indicates if we should use the FPSCR rounding
3778 // mode or the default Round to Zero mode.
3779 VFPRoundingMode mode = (instr->Bit(7) != 1) ? FPSCR_rounding_mode_ : RZ;
3780 DCHECK((mode == RM) || (mode == RZ) || (mode == RN));
3781
3782 bool unsigned_integer = (instr->Bit(16) == 0);
3783 bool double_precision = (src_precision == kDoublePrecision);
3784
3785 double val = double_precision ? get_double_from_d_register(src).get_scalar()
3786 : get_float_from_s_register(src).get_scalar();
3787
3788 int32_t temp = ConvertDoubleToInt(val, unsigned_integer, mode);
3789
3790 // Update the destination register.
3791 set_s_register_from_sinteger(dst, temp);
3792
3793 } else {
3794 bool unsigned_integer = (instr->Bit(7) == 0);
3795
3796 int dst = instr->VFPDRegValue(src_precision);
3797 int src = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3798
3799 int val = get_sinteger_from_s_register(src);
3800
3801 if (src_precision == kDoublePrecision) {
3802 if (unsigned_integer) {
3803 set_d_register_from_double(
3804 dst, static_cast<double>(static_cast<uint32_t>(val)));
3805 } else {
3806 set_d_register_from_double(dst, static_cast<double>(val));
3807 }
3808 } else {
3809 if (unsigned_integer) {
3810 set_s_register_from_float(
3811 dst, static_cast<float>(static_cast<uint32_t>(val)));
3812 } else {
3813 set_s_register_from_float(dst, static_cast<float>(val));
3814 }
3815 }
3816 }
3817}
3818
3819// void Simulator::DecodeType6CoprocessorIns(Instruction* instr)
3820// Decode Type 6 coprocessor instructions.
3821// Dm = vmov(Rt, Rt2)
3822// <Rt, Rt2> = vmov(Dm)
3823// Ddst = MEM(Rbase + 4*offset).
3824// MEM(Rbase + 4*offset) = Dsrc.
3825void Simulator::DecodeType6CoprocessorIns(Instruction* instr) {
3826 DCHECK_EQ(instr->TypeValue(), 6);
3827
3828 if (instr->CoprocessorValue() == 0xA) {
3829 switch (instr->OpcodeValue()) {
3830 case 0x8:
3831 case 0xA:
3832 case 0xC:
3833 case 0xE: { // Load and store single precision float to memory.
3834 int rn = instr->RnValue();
3835 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
3836 int offset = instr->Immed8Value();
3837 if (!instr->HasU()) {
3838 offset = -offset;
3839 }
3840
3841 int32_t address = get_register(rn) + 4 * offset;
3842 // Load and store address for singles must be at least four-byte
3843 // aligned.
3844 DCHECK_EQ(address % 4, 0);
3845 if (instr->HasL()) {
3846 // Load single from memory: vldr.
3847 set_s_register_from_sinteger(vd, ReadW(address));
3848 } else {
3849 // Store single to memory: vstr.
3850 WriteW(address, get_sinteger_from_s_register(vd));
3851 }
3852 break;
3853 }
3854 case 0x4:
3855 case 0x5:
3856 case 0x6:
3857 case 0x7:
3858 case 0x9:
3859 case 0xB:
3860 // Load/store multiple single from memory: vldm/vstm.
3861 HandleVList(instr);
3862 break;
3863 default:
3864 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3865 }
3866 } else if (instr->CoprocessorValue() == 0xB) {
3867 switch (instr->OpcodeValue()) {
3868 case 0x2:
3869 // Load and store double to two GP registers
3870 if (instr->Bits(7, 6) != 0 || instr->Bit(4) != 1) {
3871 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3872 } else {
3873 int rt = instr->RtValue();
3874 int rn = instr->RnValue();
3875 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3876 if (instr->HasL()) {
3877 uint32_t data[2];
3878 get_d_register(vm, data);
3879 set_register(rt, data[0]);
3880 set_register(rn, data[1]);
3881 } else {
3882 int32_t data[] = {get_register(rt), get_register(rn)};
3883 set_d_register(vm, reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(data));
3884 }
3885 }
3886 break;
3887 case 0x8:
3888 case 0xA:
3889 case 0xC:
3890 case 0xE: { // Load and store double to memory.
3891 int rn = instr->RnValue();
3892 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
3893 int offset = instr->Immed8Value();
3894 if (!instr->HasU()) {
3895 offset = -offset;
3896 }
3897 int32_t address = get_register(rn) + 4 * offset;
3898 // Load and store address for doubles must be at least four-byte
3899 // aligned.
3900 DCHECK_EQ(address % 4, 0);
3901 if (instr->HasL()) {
3902 // Load double from memory: vldr.
3903 int32_t data[] = {ReadW(address), ReadW(address + 4)};
3904 set_d_register(vd, reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(data));
3905 } else {
3906 // Store double to memory: vstr.
3907 uint32_t data[2];
3908 get_d_register(vd, data);
3909 WriteW(address, data[0]);
3910 WriteW(address + 4, data[1]);
3911 }
3912 break;
3913 }
3914 case 0x4:
3915 case 0x5:
3916 case 0x6:
3917 case 0x7:
3918 case 0x9:
3919 case 0xB:
3920 // Load/store multiple double from memory: vldm/vstm.
3921 HandleVList(instr);
3922 break;
3923 default:
3924 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3925 }
3926 } else {
3927 UNIMPLEMENTED(); // Not used by V8.
3928 }
3929}

3931// Helper functions for implementing NEON ops. Unop applies a unary op to each
3932// lane. Binop applies a binary operation to matching input lanes.
3933template <typename T, int SIZE = kSimd128Size>
3934void Unop(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, std::function<T(T)> unop) {
3935 static const int kLanes = SIZE / sizeof(T);
3936 T src[kLanes];
3937 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src);
3938 for (int i = 0; i < kLanes; i++) {
3939 src[i] = unop(src[i]);
3940 }
3941 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src);
3942}
3943
3944template <typename T, int SIZE = kSimd128Size>
3945void Binop(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn,
3946 std::function<T(T, T)> binop) {
3947 static const int kLanes = SIZE / sizeof(T);
3948 T src1[kLanes], src2[kLanes];
3949 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vn, src1);
3950 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src2);
3951 for (int i = 0; i < kLanes; i++) {
3952 src1[i] = binop(src1[i], src2[i]);
3953 }
3954 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src1);
3955}

3957// Templated operations for NEON instructions.
3958template <typename T, typename U>
3959U Widen(T value) {
3960 static_assert(sizeof(int64_t) > sizeof(T), "T must be int32_t or smaller");
3961 static_assert(sizeof(U) > sizeof(T), "T must smaller than U");
3962 return static_cast<U>(value);
3963}
3964
3965template <typename T, typename U>
3966void Widen(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
3967 static const int kLanes = 8 / sizeof(T);
3968 T src[kLanes];
3969 U dst[kLanes];
3970 simulator->get_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vm, src);
3971 for (int i = 0; i < kLanes; i++) {
3972 dst[i] = Widen<T, U>(src[i]);
3973 }
3974 simulator->set_neon_register(Vd, dst);
3975}

4012template <typename T, int SIZE>
4013void Zip(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
4014 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4015 static const int kPairs = kElems / 2;
4016 T src1[kElems], src2[kElems], dst1[kElems], dst2[kElems];
4017 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src1);
4018 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src2);
4019 for (int i = 0; i < kPairs; i++) {
4020 dst1[i * 2] = src1[i];
4021 dst1[i * 2 + 1] = src2[i];
4022 dst2[i * 2] = src1[i + kPairs];
4023 dst2[i * 2 + 1] = src2[i + kPairs];
4024 }
4025 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, dst1);
4026 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, dst2);
4027}

4029template <typename T, int SIZE>
4030void Unzip(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
4031 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4032 static const int kPairs = kElems / 2;
4033 T src1[kElems], src2[kElems], dst1[kElems], dst2[kElems];
4034 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src1);
4035 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src2);
4036 for (int i = 0; i < kPairs; i++) {
4037 dst1[i] = src1[i * 2];
4038 dst1[i + kPairs] = src2[i * 2];
4039 dst2[i] = src1[i * 2 + 1];
4040 dst2[i + kPairs] = src2[i * 2 + 1];

4043 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, dst2);

4046template <typename T, int SIZE>
4047void Transpose(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
4048 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4049 static const int kPairs = kElems / 2;
4050 T src1[kElems], src2[kElems];
4051 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src1);
4052 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src2);
4053 for (int i = 0; i < kPairs; i++) {
4054 std::swap(src1[2 * i + 1], src2[2 * i]);
4055 }
4056 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src1);
4057 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src2);

4086void VmovImmediate(Simulator* simulator, Instruction* instr) {
4087 uint8_t cmode = instr->Bits(11, 8);
4088 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4089 int q = instr->Bit(6);
4090 int regs = q ? 2 : 1;
4091 uint8_t imm = instr->Bit(24) << 7; // i
4092 imm |= instr->Bits(18, 16) << 4; // imm3
4093 imm |= instr->Bits(3, 0); // imm4
4094 switch (cmode) {
4095 case 0: {
4096 // Set the LSB of each 64-bit halves.
4097 uint64_t imm64 = imm;
4098 for (int r = 0; r < regs; r++) {
4099 simulator->set_d_register(vd + r, &imm64);
4100 }
4101 break;
4102 }
4103 case 0xe: {
4104 uint8_t imms[kSimd128Size];
4105 // Set all bytes of register.
4106 std::fill_n(imms, kSimd128Size, imm);
4107 uint64_t imm64;
4108 memcpy(&imm64, imms, 8);
4109 for (int r = 0; r < regs; r++) {
4110 simulator->set_d_register(vd + r, &imm64);
4111 }
4112 break;
4113 }
4114 default: {
4115 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4116 }
4117 }
4118}

4174}
4175
4176template <typename T, int SIZE>
4177void ShiftLeftAndInsert(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int shift) {
4178 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4179 T src[kElems];
4180 T dst[kElems];
4181 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src);
4182 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4183 uint64_t mask = (1llu << shift) - 1llu;
4184 for (int i = 0; i < kElems; i++) {
4185 dst[i] = (src[i] << shift) | (dst[i] & mask);
4186 }
4187 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4188}
4189
4190template <typename T, int SIZE>
4191void ShiftRightAndInsert(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int shift) {
4192 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4193 T src[kElems];
4194 T dst[kElems];
4195 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src);
4196 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4197 uint64_t mask = ~((1llu << (kBitsPerByte * SIZE - shift)) - 1llu);
4198 for (int i = 0; i < kElems; i++) {
4199 dst[i] = (src[i] >> shift) | (dst[i] & mask);
4200 }
4201 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4202}
4203
4204template <typename T, typename S_T, int SIZE>
4205void ShiftByRegister(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn) {
4206 static const int kElems = SIZE / sizeof(T);
4207 T src[kElems];
4208 S_T shift[kElems];
4209 simulator->get_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vm, src);
4210 simulator->get_neon_register<S_T, SIZE>(Vn, shift);
4211 for (int i = 0; i < kElems; i++) {
4212 // Take lowest 8 bits of shift value (see F6.1.217 of ARM Architecture
4213 // Reference Manual ARMv8), as signed 8-bit value.
4214 int8_t shift_value = static_cast<int8_t>(shift[i]);
4215 int size = static_cast<int>(sizeof(T) * 8);
4216 // When shift value is greater/equal than size, we end up relying on
4217 // undefined behavior, handle that and emulate what the hardware does.
4218 if ((shift_value) >= 0) {
4219 // If the shift value is greater/equal than size, zero out the result.
4220 if (shift_value >= size) {
4221 src[i] = 0;
4222 } else {
4223 using unsignedT = std::make_unsigned_t<T>;
4224 src[i] = static_cast<unsignedT>(src[i]) << shift_value;
4225 }
4226 } else {
4227 // If the shift value is greater/equal than size, always end up with -1.
4228 if (-shift_value >= size) {
4229 src[i] = -1;
4230 } else {
4231 src[i] = ArithmeticShiftRight(src[i], -shift_value);
4232 }
4233 }
4234 }
4235 simulator->set_neon_register<T, SIZE>(Vd, src);
4236}

4239void CompareEqual(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn) {
4240 Binop<T>(simulator, Vd, Vm, Vn, [](T x, T y) { return x == y ? -1 : 0; });
4241}

4243template <typename T, int SIZE>
4244void CompareGreater(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn, bool ge) {
4245 if (ge) {
4246 Binop<T>(simulator, Vd, Vm, Vn, [](T x, T y) { return x >= y ? -1 : 0; });
4247 } else {
4248 Binop<T>(simulator, Vd, Vm, Vn, [](T x, T y) { return x > y ? -1 : 0; });
4249 }

4252float MinMax(float a, float b, bool is_min) {
4253 return is_min ? JSMin(a, b) : JSMax(a, b);
4254}
4255template <typename T>
4256T MinMax(T a, T b, bool is_min) {
4257 return is_min ? std::min(a, b) : std::max(a, b);
4258}
4259
4260template <typename T, int SIZE>
4261void MinMax(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn, bool min) {
4262 if (min) {
4263 Binop<T>(simulator, Vd, Vm, Vn,
4264 [](auto x, auto y) { return std::min<T>(x, y); });
4265 } else {
4266 Binop<T>(simulator, Vd, Vm, Vn,
4267 [](auto x, auto y) { return std::max<T>(x, y); });
4268 }
4269}

4271template <typename T>
4272void PairwiseMinMax(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn, bool min) {
4273 static const int kElems = kDoubleSize / sizeof(T);
4274 static const int kPairs = kElems / 2;
4275 T dst[kElems], src1[kElems], src2[kElems];
4276 simulator->get_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vn, src1);
4277 simulator->get_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vm, src2);
4278 for (int i = 0; i < kPairs; i++) {
4279 dst[i] = MinMax(src1[i * 2], src1[i * 2 + 1], min);
4280 dst[i + kPairs] = MinMax(src2[i * 2], src2[i * 2 + 1], min);
4281 }
4282 simulator->set_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vd, dst);
4283}

4285template <typename T>
4286void PairwiseAdd(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm, int Vn) {
4287 static const int kElems = kDoubleSize / sizeof(T);
4288 static const int kPairs = kElems / 2;
4289 T dst[kElems], src1[kElems], src2[kElems];
4290 simulator->get_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vn, src1);
4291 simulator->get_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vm, src2);
4292 for (int i = 0; i < kPairs; i++) {
4293 dst[i] = src1[i * 2] + src1[i * 2 + 1];
4294 dst[i + kPairs] = src2[i * 2] + src2[i * 2 + 1];
4295 }
4296 simulator->set_neon_register<T, kDoubleSize>(Vd, dst);
4297}

4299template <typename NarrowType, typename WideType, int SIZE = kSimd128Size>
4300void PairwiseAddLong(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
4301 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(WideType), 2 * sizeof(NarrowType));
4302 static constexpr int kSElems = SIZE / sizeof(NarrowType);
4303 static constexpr int kTElems = SIZE / sizeof(WideType);
4304 NarrowType src[kSElems];
4305 WideType dst[kTElems];
4306 simulator->get_neon_register<NarrowType, SIZE>(Vm, src);
4307 for (int i = 0; i < kTElems; i++) {
4308 dst[i] = WideType{src[i * 2]} + WideType{src[i * 2 + 1]};
4309 }
4310 simulator->set_neon_register<WideType, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4311}
