4313template <typename NarrowType, typename WideType, int SIZE = kSimd128Size>
4314void PairwiseAddAccumulateLong(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vm) {
4315 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(WideType), 2 * sizeof(NarrowType));
4316 static constexpr int kSElems = SIZE / sizeof(NarrowType);
4317 static constexpr int kTElems = SIZE / sizeof(WideType);
4318 NarrowType src[kSElems];
4319 WideType dst[kTElems];
4320 simulator->get_neon_register<NarrowType, SIZE>(Vm, src);
4321 simulator->get_neon_register<WideType, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4322 for (int i = 0; i < kTElems; i++) {
4323 dst[i] += WideType{src[i * 2]} + WideType{src[i * 2 + 1]};
4324 }
4325 simulator->set_neon_register<WideType, SIZE>(Vd, dst);
4326}
4327
4328template <typename NarrowType, typename WideType>
4329void MultiplyLong(Simulator* simulator, int Vd, int Vn, int Vm) {
4330 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(WideType), 2 * sizeof(NarrowType));
4331 static const int kElems = kSimd128Size / sizeof(WideType);
4332 NarrowType src1[kElems], src2[kElems];
4333 WideType dst[kElems];
4334
4335 // Get the entire d reg, then memcpy it to an array so we can address the
4336 // underlying datatype easily.
4337 uint64_t tmp;
4338 simulator->get_d_register(Vn, &tmp);
4339 memcpy(src1, &tmp, sizeof(tmp));
4340 simulator->get_d_register(Vm, &tmp);
4341 memcpy(src2, &tmp, sizeof(tmp));
4342
4343 for (int i = 0; i < kElems; i++) {
4344 dst[i] = WideType{src1[i]} * WideType{src2[i]};
4345 }
4346
4347 simulator->set_neon_register<WideType>(Vd, dst);
4348}
4349
4350void Simulator::DecodeUnconditional(Instruction* instr) {
4351 // This follows the decoding in F4.1.18 Unconditional instructions.
4352 int op0 = instr->Bits(26, 25);
4353 int op1 = instr->Bit(20);
4354
4355 // Four classes of decoding:
4356 // - Miscellaneous (omitted, no instructions used in V8).
4357 // - Advanced SIMD data-processing.
4358 // - Memory hints and barriers.
4359 // - Advanced SIMD element or structure load/store.
4360 if (op0 == 0b01) {
4361 DecodeAdvancedSIMDDataProcessing(instr);
4362 } else if ((op0 & 0b10) == 0b10 && op1) {
4363 DecodeMemoryHintsAndBarriers(instr);
4364 } else if (op0 == 0b10 && !op1) {
4365 DecodeAdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStore(instr);
4366 } else {
4367 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4368 }
4369}
4370
4371void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDTwoOrThreeRegisters(Instruction* instr) {
4372 // Advanced SIMD two registers, or three registers of different lengths.
4373 int op0 = instr->Bit(24);
4374 int op1 = instr->Bits(21, 20);
4375 int op2 = instr->Bits(11, 10);
4376 int op3 = instr->Bit(6);
4377 if (!op0 && op1 == 0b11) {
4378 // vext.8 Qd, Qm, Qn, imm4
4379 int imm4 = instr->Bits(11, 8);
4380 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4381 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4382 int Vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4383 uint8_t src1[16], src2[16], dst[16];
4384 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
4385 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
4386 int boundary = kSimd128Size - imm4;
4387 int i = 0;
4388 for (; i < boundary; i++) {
4389 dst[i] = src1[i + imm4];
4390 }
4391 for (; i < 16; i++) {
4392 dst[i] = src2[i - boundary];
4393 }
4394 set_neon_register(Vd, dst);
4395 } else if (op0 && op1 == 0b11 && ((op2 >> 1) == 0)) {
4396 // Advanced SIMD two registers misc
4397 int size = instr->Bits(19, 18);
4398 int opc1 = instr->Bits(17, 16);
4399 int opc2 = instr->Bits(10, 7);
4400 int q = instr->Bit(6);
4401
4402 if (opc1 == 0 && (opc2 >> 2) == 0) {
4403 // vrev<op>.size Qd, Qm
4404 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4405 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4406 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(19, 18));
4407 NeonSize op =
4408 static_cast<NeonSize>(static_cast<int>(Neon64) - instr->Bits(8, 7));
4409 switch (op) {
4410 case Neon16: {
4411 DCHECK_EQ(Neon8, size);
4412 uint8_t src[16];
4413 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4414 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i += 2) {
4415 std::swap(src[i], src[i + 1]);
4416 }
4417 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4418 break;
4419 }
4420 case Neon32: {
4421 switch (size) {
4422 case Neon16: {
4423 uint16_t src[8];
4424 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4425 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i += 2) {
4426 std::swap(src[i], src[i + 1]);
4427 }
4428 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4429 break;
4430 }
4431 case Neon8: {
4432 uint8_t src[16];
4433 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4434 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4435 std::swap(src[i * 4], src[i * 4 + 3]);
4436 std::swap(src[i * 4 + 1], src[i * 4 + 2]);
4437 }
4438 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4439 break;
4440 }
4441 default:
4442 UNREACHABLE();
4443 }
4444 break;
4445 }
4446 case Neon64: {
4447 switch (size) {
4448 case Neon32: {
4449 uint32_t src[4];
4450 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4451 std::swap(src[0], src[1]);
4452 std::swap(src[2], src[3]);
4453 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4454 break;
4455 }
4456 case Neon16: {
4457 uint16_t src[8];
4458 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4459 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
4460 std::swap(src[i * 4], src[i * 4 + 3]);
4461 std::swap(src[i * 4 + 1], src[i * 4 + 2]);
4462 }
4463 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4464 break;
4465 }
4466 case Neon8: {
4467 uint8_t src[16];
4468 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4469 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4470 std::swap(src[i], src[7 - i]);
4471 std::swap(src[i + 8], src[15 - i]);
4472 }
4473 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4474 break;
4475 }
4476 default:
4477 UNREACHABLE();
4478 }
4479 break;
4480 }
4481 default:
4482 UNREACHABLE();
4483 }
4484 } else if (opc1 == 0 && (opc2 == 0b0100 || opc2 == 0b0101)) {
4485 DCHECK_EQ(1, instr->Bit(6)); // Only support Q regs.
4486 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4487 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4488 int is_signed = instr->Bit(7) == 0;
4489 // vpaddl Qd, Qm.
4490 switch (size) {
4491 case Neon8:
4492 is_signed ? PairwiseAddLong<int8_t, int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4493 : PairwiseAddLong<uint8_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4494 break;
4495 case Neon16:
4496 is_signed ? PairwiseAddLong<int16_t, int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4497 : PairwiseAddLong<uint16_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4498 break;
4499 case Neon32:
4500 is_signed ? PairwiseAddLong<int32_t, int64_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4501 : PairwiseAddLong<uint32_t, uint64_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4502 break;
4503 case Neon64:
4504 UNREACHABLE();
4505 }
4506 } else if (opc1 == 0 && (opc2 == 0b1100 || opc2 == 0b1101)) {
4507 DCHECK_EQ(1, instr->Bit(6)); // Only support Q regs.
4508 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4509 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4510 int is_signed = instr->Bit(7) == 0;
4511 // vpadal Qd, Qm
4512 switch (size) {
4513 case Neon8:
4514 is_signed
4515 ? PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<int8_t, int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4516 : PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<uint8_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4517 break;
4518 case Neon16:
4519 is_signed
4520 ? PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<int16_t, int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4521 : PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<uint16_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4522 break;
4523 case Neon32:
4524 is_signed
4525 ? PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<int32_t, int64_t>(this, Vd, Vm)
4526 : PairwiseAddAccumulateLong<uint32_t, uint64_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4527 break;
4528 case Neon64:
4529 UNREACHABLE();
4530 }
4531 } else if (size == 0 && opc1 == 0b10 && opc2 == 0) {
4532 if (instr->Bit(6) == 0) {
4533 // vswp Dd, Dm.
4534 uint64_t dval, mval;
4535 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4536 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4537 get_d_register(vd, &dval);
4538 get_d_register(vm, &mval);
4539 set_d_register(vm, &dval);
4540 set_d_register(vd, &mval);
4541 } else {
4542 // vswp Qd, Qm.
4543 uint32_t dval[4], mval[4];
4544 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4545 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4546 get_neon_register(vd, dval);
4547 get_neon_register(vm, mval);
4548 set_neon_register(vm, dval);
4549 set_neon_register(vd, mval);
4550 }
4551 } else if (opc1 == 0 && opc2 == 0b1010) {
4552 // vcnt Qd, Qm.
4553 DCHECK_EQ(0, size);
4554 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(q ? kSimd128Precision : kDoublePrecision);
4555 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(q ? kSimd128Precision : kDoublePrecision);
4556 uint8_t q_data[16];
4557 get_neon_register(vm, q_data);
4558 for (int i = 0; i < 16; i++) {
4559 q_data[i] = base::bits::CountPopulation(q_data[i]);
4560 }
4561 set_neon_register(vd, q_data);
4562 } else if (opc1 == 0 && opc2 == 0b1011) {
4563 // vmvn Qd, Qm.
4564 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4565 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4566 uint32_t q_data[4];
4567 get_neon_register(vm, q_data);
4568 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) q_data[i] = ~q_data[i];
4569 set_neon_register(vd, q_data);
4570 } else if (opc1 == 0b01 && opc2 == 0b0010) {
4571 // vceq.<dt> Qd, Qm, #0 (signed integers).
4572 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4573 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4574 switch (size) {
4575 case Neon8:
4576 Unop<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, [](int8_t x) { return x == 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4577 break;
4578 case Neon16:
4579 Unop<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm,
4580 [](int16_t x) { return x == 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4581 break;
4582 case Neon32:
4583 Unop<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm,
4584 [](int32_t x) { return x == 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4585 break;
4586 case Neon64:
4587 UNREACHABLE();
4588 }
4589 } else if (opc1 == 0b01 && opc2 == 0b0100) {
4590 // vclt.<dt> Qd, Qm, #0 (signed integers).
4591 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4592 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4593 switch (size) {
4594 case Neon8:
4595 Unop<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, [](int8_t x) { return x < 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4596 break;
4597 case Neon16:
4598 Unop<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, [](int16_t x) { return x < 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4599 break;
4600 case Neon32:
4601 Unop<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, [](int32_t x) { return x < 0 ? -1 : 0; });
4602 break;
4603 case Neon64:
4604 UNREACHABLE();
4605 }
4606 } else if (opc1 == 0b01 && (opc2 & 0b0111) == 0b110) {
4607 // vabs<type>.<size> Qd, Qm
4608 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4609 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4610 if (instr->Bit(10) != 0) {
4611 // floating point (clear sign bits)
4612 uint32_t src[4];
4613 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4614 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4615 src[i] &= ~0x80000000;
4616 }
4617 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4618 } else {
4619 // signed integer
4620 switch (size) {
4621 case Neon8:
4622 Abs<int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4623 break;
4624 case Neon16:
4625 Abs<int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4626 break;
4627 case Neon32:
4628 Abs<int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4629 break;
4630 default:
4631 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4632 }
4633 }
4634 } else if (opc1 == 0b01 && (opc2 & 0b0111) == 0b111) {
4635 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4636 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4637 // vneg<type>.<size> Qd, Qm (signed integer)
4638 if (instr->Bit(10) != 0) {
4639 // floating point (toggle sign bits)
4640 uint32_t src[4];
4641 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4642 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4643 src[i] ^= 0x80000000;
4644 }
4645 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4646 } else {
4647 // signed integer
4648 switch (size) {
4649 case Neon8:
4650 Neg<int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4651 break;
4652 case Neon16:
4653 Neg<int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4654 break;
4655 case Neon32:
4656 Neg<int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4657 break;
4658 default:
4659 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4660 }
4661 }
4662 } else if (opc1 == 0b10 && opc2 == 0b0001) {
4663 if (q) {
4664 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4665 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4666 // vtrn.<size> Qd, Qm.
4667 switch (size) {
4668 case Neon8:
4669 Transpose<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4670 break;
4671 case Neon16:
4672 Transpose<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4673 break;
4674 case Neon32:
4675 Transpose<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4676 break;
4677 default:
4678 UNREACHABLE();
4679 }
4680 } else {
4681 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4682 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4683 // vtrn.<size> Dd, Dm.
4684 switch (size) {
4685 case Neon8:
4686 Transpose<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4687 break;
4688 case Neon16:
4689 Transpose<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4690 break;
4691 case Neon32:
4692 Transpose<uint32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4693 break;
4694 default:
4695 UNREACHABLE();
4696 }
4697 }
4698 } else if (opc1 == 0b10 && (opc2 & 0b1110) == 0b0010) {
4699 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(19, 18));
4700 if (q) {
4701 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4702 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4703 if (instr->Bit(7) == 1) {
4704 // vzip.<size> Qd, Qm.
4705 switch (size) {
4706 case Neon8:
4707 Zip<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4708 break;
4709 case Neon16:
4710 Zip<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4711 break;
4712 case Neon32:
4713 Zip<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4714 break;
4715 default:
4716 UNREACHABLE();
4717 }
4718 } else {
4719 // vuzp.<size> Qd, Qm.
4720 switch (size) {
4721 case Neon8:
4722 Unzip<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4723 break;
4724 case Neon16:
4725 Unzip<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4726 break;
4727 case Neon32:
4728 Unzip<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm);
4729 break;
4730 default:
4731 UNREACHABLE();
4732 }
4733 }
4734 } else {
4735 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4736 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4737 if (instr->Bit(7) == 1) {
4738 // vzip.<size> Dd, Dm.
4739 switch (size) {
4740 case Neon8:
4741 Zip<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4742 break;
4743 case Neon16:
4744 Zip<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4745 break;
4746 case Neon32:
4747 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4748 default:
4749 UNREACHABLE();
4750 }
4751 } else {
4752 // vuzp.<size> Dd, Dm.
4753 switch (size) {
4754 case Neon8:
4755 Unzip<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4756 break;
4757 case Neon16:
4758 Unzip<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm);
4759 break;
4760 case Neon32:
4761 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4762 default:
4763 UNREACHABLE();
4764 }
4765 }
4766 }
4767 } else if (opc1 == 0b10 && (opc2 & 0b1110) == 0b0100) {
4768 // vqmovn.<type><size> Dd, Qm.
4769 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4770 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4771 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(19, 18));
4772 bool dst_unsigned = instr->Bit(6) != 0;
4773 bool src_unsigned = instr->Bits(7, 6) == 0b11;
4774 DCHECK_IMPLIES(src_unsigned, dst_unsigned);
4775 switch (size) {
4776 case Neon8: {
4777 if (src_unsigned) {
4778 SaturatingNarrow<uint16_t, uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4779 } else if (dst_unsigned) {
4780 SaturatingNarrow<int16_t, uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4781 } else {
4782 SaturatingNarrow<int16_t, int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4783 }
4784 break;
4785 }
4786 case Neon16: {
4787 if (src_unsigned) {
4788 SaturatingNarrow<uint32_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4789 } else if (dst_unsigned) {
4790 SaturatingNarrow<int32_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4791 } else {
4792 SaturatingNarrow<int32_t, int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4793 }
4794 break;
4795 }
4796 case Neon32: {
4797 if (src_unsigned) {
4798 SaturatingNarrow<uint64_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4799 } else if (dst_unsigned) {
4800 SaturatingNarrow<int64_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4801 } else {
4802 SaturatingNarrow<int64_t, int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
4803 }
4804 break;
4805 }
4806 case Neon64:
4807 UNREACHABLE();
4808 }
4809 } else if (opc1 == 0b10 && instr->Bit(10) == 1) {
4810 // vrint<q>.<dt> <Dd>, <Dm>
4811 // vrint<q>.<dt> <Qd>, <Qm>
4812 // See F6.1.205
4813 int regs = instr->Bit(6) + 1;
4814 int rounding_mode = instr->Bits(9, 7);
4815 float (*fproundint)(float) = nullptr;
4816 switch (rounding_mode) {
4817 case 0:
4818 fproundint = &nearbyintf;
4819 break;
4820 case 3:
4821 fproundint = &truncf;
4822 break;
4823 case 5:
4824 fproundint = &floorf;
4825 break;
4826 case 7:
4827 fproundint = &ceilf;
4828 break;
4829 default:
4830 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4831 }
4832 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4833 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4834
4835 float floats[2];
4836 for (int r = 0; r < regs; r++) {
4837 // We cannot simply use GetVFPSingleValue since our Q registers
4838 // might not map to any S registers at all.
4839 get_neon_register<float, kDoubleSize>(vm + r, floats);
4840 for (int e = 0; e < 2; e++) {
4841 floats[e] = canonicalizeNaN(fproundint(floats[e]));
4842 }
4843 set_neon_register<float, kDoubleSize>(vd + r, floats);
4844 }
4845 } else if (opc1 == 0b11 && (opc2 & 0b1100) == 0b1000) {
4846 // vrecpe/vrsqrte.f32 Qd, Qm.
4847 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4848 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4849 uint32_t src[4];
4850 get_neon_register(Vm, src);
4851 if (instr->Bit(7) == 0) {
4852 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4853 float denom = base::bit_cast<float>(src[i]);
4854 div_zero_vfp_flag_ = (denom == 0);
4855 float result = 1.0f / denom;
4856 result = canonicalizeNaN(result);
4857 src[i] = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(result);
4858 }
4859 } else {
4860 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4861 float radicand = base::bit_cast<float>(src[i]);
4862 float result = 1.0f / std::sqrt(radicand);
4863 result = canonicalizeNaN(result);
4864 src[i] = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(result);
4865 }
4866 }
4867 set_neon_register(Vd, src);
4868 } else if (opc1 == 0b11 && (opc2 & 0b1100) == 0b1100) {
4869 // vcvt.<Td>.<Tm> Qd, Qm.
4870 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4871 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4872 uint32_t q_data[4];
4873 get_neon_register(Vm, q_data);
4874 int op = instr->Bits(8, 7);
4875 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
4876 switch (op) {
4877 case 0:
4878 // f32 <- s32, round towards nearest.
4879 q_data[i] = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(std::round(
4880 static_cast<float>(base::bit_cast<int32_t>(q_data[i]))));
4881 break;
4882 case 1:
4883 // f32 <- u32, round towards nearest.
4884 q_data[i] = base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(
4885 std::round(static_cast<float>(q_data[i])));
4886 break;
4887 case 2:
4888 // s32 <- f32, round to zero.
4889 q_data[i] = static_cast<uint32_t>(ConvertDoubleToInt(
4890 base::bit_cast<float>(q_data[i]), false, RZ));
4891 break;
4892 case 3:
4893 // u32 <- f32, round to zero.
4894 q_data[i] = static_cast<uint32_t>(
4895 ConvertDoubleToInt(base::bit_cast<float>(q_data[i]), true, RZ));
4896 break;
4897 }
4898 }
4899 set_neon_register(Vd, q_data);
4900 } else {
4901 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4902 }
4903 } else if (op0 && op1 == 0b11 && op2 == 0b10) {
4904 // vtb[l,x] Dd, <list>, Dm.
4905 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4906 int vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4907 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4908 int table_len = (instr->Bits(9, 8) + 1) * kDoubleSize;
4909 bool vtbx = instr->Bit(6) != 0; // vtbl / vtbx
4910 uint64_t destination = 0, indices = 0, result = 0;
4911 get_d_register(vd, &destination);
4912 get_d_register(vm, &indices);
4913 for (int i = 0; i < kDoubleSize; i++) {
4914 int shift = i * kBitsPerByte;
4915 int index = (indices >> shift) & 0xFF;
4916 if (index < table_len) {
4917 uint64_t table;
4918 get_d_register(vn + index / kDoubleSize, &table);
4919 result |= ((table >> ((index % kDoubleSize) * kBitsPerByte)) & 0xFF)
4920 << shift;
4921 } else if (vtbx) {
4922 result |= destination & (0xFFull << shift);
4923 }
4924 }
4925 set_d_register(vd, &result);
4926 } else if (op0 && op1 == 0b11 && op2 == 0b11) {
4927 // Advanced SIMD duplicate (scalar)
4928 if (instr->Bits(9, 7) == 0) {
4929 // vdup.<size> Dd, Dm[index].
4930 // vdup.<size> Qd, Dm[index].
4931 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4932 int imm4 = instr->Bits(19, 16);
4933 int size = 0, index = 0, mask = 0;
4934 if ((imm4 & 0x1) != 0) {
4935 size = 8;
4936 index = imm4 >> 1;
4937 mask = 0xFFu;
4938 } else if ((imm4 & 0x2) != 0) {
4939 size = 16;
4940 index = imm4 >> 2;
4941 mask = 0xFFFFu;
4942 } else {
4943 size = 32;
4944 index = imm4 >> 3;
4945 mask = 0xFFFFFFFFu;
4946 }
4947 uint64_t d_data;
4948 get_d_register(vm, &d_data);
4949 uint32_t scalar = (d_data >> (size * index)) & mask;
4950 uint32_t duped = scalar;
4951 for (int i = 1; i < 32 / size; i++) {
4952 scalar <<= size;
4953 duped |= scalar;
4954 }
4955 uint32_t result[4] = {duped, duped, duped, duped};
4956 if (instr->Bit(6) == 0) {
4957 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4958 set_d_register(vd, result);
4959 } else {
4960 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4961 set_neon_register(vd, result);
4962 }
4963 } else {
4964 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4965 }
4966 } else if (op1 != 0b11 && !op3) {
4967 // Advanced SIMD three registers of different lengths.
4968 int u = instr->Bit(24);
4969 int opc = instr->Bits(11, 8);
4970 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
4971 if (opc == 0b1000) {
4972 // vmlal.u<size> Qd, Dn, Dm
4973 if (size != Neon32) UNIMPLEMENTED();
4974
4975 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4976 int Vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4977 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4978 uint64_t src1, src2, dst[2];
4979
4980 get_neon_register<uint64_t>(Vd, dst);
4981 get_d_register(Vn, &src1);
4982 get_d_register(Vm, &src2);
4983 dst[0] += (src1 & 0xFFFFFFFFULL) * (src2 & 0xFFFFFFFFULL);
4984 dst[1] += (src1 >> 32) * (src2 >> 32);
4985 set_neon_register<uint64_t>(Vd, dst);
4986 } else if (opc == 0b1100) {
4987 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
4988 int Vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4989 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
4990 if (u) {
4991 // vmull.u<size> Qd, Dn, Dm
4992 switch (size) {
4993 case Neon8: {
4994 MultiplyLong<uint8_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
4995 break;
4996 }
4997 case Neon16: {
4998 MultiplyLong<uint16_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
4999 break;
5000 }
5001 case Neon32: {
5002 MultiplyLong<uint32_t, uint64_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
5003 break;
5004 }
5005 case Neon64: {
5006 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5007 }
5008 }
5009 } else {
5010 // vmull.s<size> Qd, Dn, Dm
5011 switch (size) {
5012 case Neon8: {
5013 MultiplyLong<int8_t, int16_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
5014 break;
5015 }
5016 case Neon16: {
5017 MultiplyLong<int16_t, int32_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
5018 break;
5019 }
5020 case Neon32: {
5021 MultiplyLong<int32_t, int64_t>(this, Vd, Vn, Vm);
5022 break;
5023 }
5024 case Neon64: {
5025 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5026 }
5027 }
5028 }
5029 }
5030 } else if (op1 != 0b11 && op3) {
5031 // The instructions specified by this encoding are not used in V8.
5032 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5033 } else {
5034 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5035 }
5036}
5037
5038void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDDataProcessing(Instruction* instr) {
5039 int op0 = instr->Bit(23);
5040 int op1 = instr->Bit(4);
5041
5042 if (op0 == 0) {
5043 // Advanced SIMD three registers of same length.
5044 int u = instr->Bit(24);
5045 int opc = instr->Bits(11, 8);
5046 int q = instr->Bit(6);
5047 int sz = instr->Bits(21, 20);
5048 int Vd, Vm, Vn;
5049 if (q) {
5050 Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5051 Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5052 Vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5053 } else {
5054 Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5055 Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5056 Vn = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5057 }
5058
5059 if (!u && opc == 0 && op1) {
5060 // vqadd.s<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5061 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5062 switch (size) {
5063 case Neon8:
5064 AddSat<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5065 break;
5066 case Neon16:
5067 AddSat<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5068 break;
5069 case Neon32:
5070 AddSat<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5071 break;
5072 default:
5073 UNREACHABLE();
5074 }
5075 } else if (!u && opc == 1 && sz == 2 && q && op1) {
5076 // vmov Qd, Qm.
5077 // vorr, Qd, Qm, Qn.
5078 uint32_t src1[4];
5079 get_neon_register(Vm, src1);
5080 if (Vm != Vn) {
5081 uint32_t src2[4];
5082 get_neon_register(Vn, src2);
5083 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5084 src1[i] = src1[i] | src2[i];
5085 }
5086 }
5087 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5088 } else if (!u && opc == 1 && sz == 3 && q && op1) {
5089 // vorn, Qd, Qm, Qn.
5090 // NeonSize does not matter.
5091 Binop<uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn,
5092 [](uint32_t x, uint32_t y) { return x | (~y); });
5093 } else if (!u && opc == 1 && sz == 0 && q && op1) {
5094 // vand Qd, Qm, Qn.
5095 uint32_t src1[4], src2[4];
5096 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5097 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5098 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5099 src1[i] = src1[i] & src2[i];
5100 }
5101 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5102 } else if (!u && opc == 1 && sz == 1 && q && op1) {
5103 // vbic Qd, Qm, Qn.
5104 uint32_t src1[4], src2[4];
5105 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5106 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5107 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5108 src1[i] = src1[i] & ~src2[i];
5109 }
5110 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5111 } else if (!u && opc == 2 && op1) {
5112 // vqsub.s<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5113 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5114 switch (size) {
5115 case Neon8:
5116 SubSat<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5117 break;
5118 case Neon16:
5119 SubSat<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5120 break;
5121 case Neon32:
5122 SubSat<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5123 break;
5124 case Neon64:
5125 SubSat<int64_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5126 break;
5127 default:
5128 UNREACHABLE();
5129 }
5130 } else if (!u && opc == 3) {
5131 // vcge/vcgt.s<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5132 bool ge = instr->Bit(4) == 1;
5133 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5134 switch (size) {
5135 case Neon8:
5136 CompareGreater<int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5137 break;
5138 case Neon16:
5139 CompareGreater<int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5140 break;
5141 case Neon32:
5142 CompareGreater<int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5143 break;
5144 default:
5145 UNREACHABLE();
5146 }
5147 } else if (!u && opc == 4 && !op1) {
5148 // vshl s<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5149 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5150 switch (size) {
5151 case Neon8:
5152 ShiftByRegister<int8_t, int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5153 break;
5154 case Neon16:
5155 ShiftByRegister<int16_t, int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5156 break;
5157 case Neon32:
5158 ShiftByRegister<int32_t, int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5159 break;
5160 case Neon64:
5161 ShiftByRegister<int64_t, int64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5162 break;
5163 default:
5164 UNREACHABLE();
5165 }
5166 } else if (!u && opc == 6) {
5167 // vmin/vmax.s<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5168 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5169 bool min = instr->Bit(4) != 0;
5170 switch (size) {
5171 case Neon8:
5172 MinMax<int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5173 break;
5174 case Neon16:
5175 MinMax<int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5176 break;
5177 case Neon32:
5178 MinMax<int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5179 break;
5180 default:
5181 UNREACHABLE();
5182 }
5183 } else if (!u && opc == 8 && op1) {
5184 // vtst.i<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5185 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5186 switch (size) {
5187 case Neon8:
5188 Test<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5189 break;
5190 case Neon16:
5191 Test<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5192 break;
5193 case Neon32:
5194 Test<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5195 break;
5196 default:
5197 UNREACHABLE();
5198 }
5199 } else if (!u && opc == 8 && !op1) {
5200 // vadd.i<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5201 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5202 switch (size) {
5203 case Neon8:
5204 Add<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5205 break;
5206 case Neon16:
5207 Add<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5208 break;
5209 case Neon32:
5210 Add<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5211 break;
5212 case Neon64:
5213 Add<uint64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5214 break;
5215 }
5216 } else if (opc == 9 && op1) {
5217 // vmul.i<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5218 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5219 switch (size) {
5220 case Neon8:
5221 Mul<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5222 break;
5223 case Neon16:
5224 Mul<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5225 break;
5226 case Neon32:
5227 Mul<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5228 break;
5229 default:
5230 UNREACHABLE();
5231 }
5232 } else if (!u && opc == 0xA) {
5233 // vpmin/vpmax.s<size> Dd, Dm, Dn.
5234 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5235 bool min = instr->Bit(4) != 0;
5236 switch (size) {
5237 case Neon8:
5238 PairwiseMinMax<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5239 break;
5240 case Neon16:
5241 PairwiseMinMax<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5242 break;
5243 case Neon32:
5244 PairwiseMinMax<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5245 break;
5246 default:
5247 UNREACHABLE();
5248 }
5249 } else if (!u && opc == 0xB) {
5250 // vpadd.i<size> Dd, Dm, Dn.
5251 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5252 switch (size) {
5253 case Neon8:
5254 PairwiseAdd<int8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5255 break;
5256 case Neon16:
5257 PairwiseAdd<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5258 break;
5259 case Neon32:
5260 PairwiseAdd<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5261 break;
5262 default:
5263 UNREACHABLE();
5264 }
5265 } else if (!u && opc == 0xD && !op1) {
5266 float src1[4], src2[4];
5267 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5268 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5269 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5270 if (instr->Bit(21) == 0) {
5271 // vadd.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn.
5272 src1[i] = src1[i] + src2[i];
5273 } else {
5274 // vsub.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn.
5275 src1[i] = src1[i] - src2[i];
5276 }
5277 }
5278 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5279 } else if (!u && opc == 0xE && !sz && !op1) {
5280 // vceq.f32.
5281 float src1[4], src2[4];
5282 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5283 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5284 uint32_t dst[4];
5285 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5286 dst[i] = (src1[i] == src2[i]) ? 0xFFFFFFFF : 0;
5287 }
5288 set_neon_register(Vd, dst);
5289 } else if (!u && opc == 0xF && op1) {
5290 float src1[4], src2[4];
5291 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5292 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5293 if (instr->Bit(21) == 0) {
5294 // vrecps.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn.
5295 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5296 src1[i] = 2.0f - src1[i] * src2[i];
5297 }
5298 } else {
5299 // vrsqrts.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn.
5300 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5301 src1[i] = (3.0f - src1[i] * src2[i]) * 0.5f;
5302 }
5303 }
5304 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5305 } else if (!u && opc == 0xF && !op1) {
5306 float src1[4], src2[4];
5307 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5308 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5309 // vmin/vmax.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn.
5310 bool min = instr->Bit(21) == 1;
5311 bool saved = FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_;
5312 FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ = true;
5313 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5314 // vmin returns default NaN if any input is NaN.
5315 src1[i] = canonicalizeNaN(MinMax(src1[i], src2[i], min));
5316 }
5317 FPSCR_default_NaN_mode_ = saved;
5318 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5319 } else if (u && opc == 0 && op1) {
5320 // vqadd.u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5321 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5322 switch (size) {
5323 case Neon8:
5324 AddSat<uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5325 break;
5326 case Neon16:
5327 AddSat<uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5328 break;
5329 case Neon32:
5330 AddSat<uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5331 break;
5332 default:
5333 UNREACHABLE();
5334 }
5335 } else if (u && opc == 1 && sz == 1 && op1) {
5336 // vbsl.size Qd, Qm, Qn.
5337 uint32_t dst[4], src1[4], src2[4];
5338 get_neon_register(Vd, dst);
5339 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5340 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5341 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5342 dst[i] = (dst[i] & src1[i]) | (~dst[i] & src2[i]);
5343 }
5344 set_neon_register(Vd, dst);
5345 } else if (u && opc == 1 && sz == 0 && !q && op1) {
5346 // veor Dd, Dn, Dm
5347 uint64_t src1, src2;
5348 get_d_register(Vn, &src1);
5349 get_d_register(Vm, &src2);
5350 src1 ^= src2;
5351 set_d_register(Vd, &src1);
5352 } else if (u && opc == 1 && sz == 0 && q && op1) {
5353 // veor Qd, Qn, Qm
5354 uint32_t src1[4], src2[4];
5355 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5356 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5357 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) src1[i] ^= src2[i];
5358 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5359 } else if (u && opc == 1 && !op1) {
5360 // vrhadd.u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5361 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5362 switch (size) {
5363 case Neon8:
5364 Binop<uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, RoundingAverageUnsigned<uint8_t>);
5365 break;
5366 case Neon16:
5367 Binop<uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, RoundingAverageUnsigned<uint16_t>);
5368 break;
5369 case Neon32:
5370 Binop<uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, RoundingAverageUnsigned<uint32_t>);
5371 break;
5372 default:
5373 UNREACHABLE();
5374 }
5375 } else if (u && opc == 2 && op1) {
5376 // vqsub.u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5377 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5378 switch (size) {
5379 case Neon8:
5380 SubSat<uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5381 break;
5382 case Neon16:
5383 SubSat<uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5384 break;
5385 case Neon32:
5386 SubSat<uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5387 break;
5388 default:
5389 UNREACHABLE();
5390 }
5391 } else if (u && opc == 3) {
5392 // vcge/vcgt.u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5393 bool ge = instr->Bit(4) == 1;
5394 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5395 switch (size) {
5396 case Neon8:
5397 CompareGreater<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5398 break;
5399 case Neon16:
5400 CompareGreater<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5401 break;
5402 case Neon32:
5403 CompareGreater<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, ge);
5404 break;
5405 default:
5406 UNREACHABLE();
5407 }
5408 } else if (u && opc == 4 && !op1) {
5409 // vshl u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5410 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5411 switch (size) {
5412 case Neon8:
5413 ShiftByRegister<uint8_t, int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5414 break;
5415 case Neon16:
5416 ShiftByRegister<uint16_t, int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5417 break;
5418 case Neon32:
5419 ShiftByRegister<uint32_t, int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5420 break;
5421 case Neon64:
5422 ShiftByRegister<uint64_t, int64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5423 break;
5424 default:
5425 UNREACHABLE();
5426 }
5427 } else if (u && opc == 6) {
5428 // vmin/vmax.u<size> Qd, Qm, Qn.
5429 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5430 bool min = instr->Bit(4) != 0;
5431 switch (size) {
5432 case Neon8:
5433 MinMax<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5434 break;
5435 case Neon16:
5436 MinMax<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5437 break;
5438 case Neon32:
5439 MinMax<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5440 break;
5441 default:
5442 UNREACHABLE();
5443 }
5444 } else if (u && opc == 8 && !op1) {
5445 // vsub.size Qd, Qm, Qn.
5446 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5447 switch (size) {
5448 case Neon8:
5449 Sub<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5450 break;
5451 case Neon16:
5452 Sub<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5453 break;
5454 case Neon32:
5455 Sub<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5456 break;
5457 case Neon64:
5458 Sub<uint64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5459 break;
5460 }
5461 } else if (u && opc == 8 && op1) {
5462 // vceq.size Qd, Qm, Qn.
5463 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5464 switch (size) {
5465 case Neon8:
5466 CompareEqual<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5467 break;
5468 case Neon16:
5469 CompareEqual<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5470 break;
5471 case Neon32:
5472 CompareEqual<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5473 break;
5474 default:
5475 UNREACHABLE();
5476 }
5477 } else if (u && opc == 0xA) {
5478 // vpmin/vpmax.u<size> Dd, Dm, Dn.
5479 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5480 bool min = instr->Bit(4) != 0;
5481 switch (size) {
5482 case Neon8:
5483 PairwiseMinMax<uint8_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5484 break;
5485 case Neon16:
5486 PairwiseMinMax<uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5487 break;
5488 case Neon32:
5489 PairwiseMinMax<uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, min);
5490 break;
5491 default:
5492 UNREACHABLE();
5493 }
5494 } else if (u && opc == 0xD && sz == 0 && q && op1) {
5495 // vmul.f32 Qd, Qn, Qm
5496 float src1[4], src2[4];
5497 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5498 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5499 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5500 src1[i] = src1[i] * src2[i];
5501 }
5502 set_neon_register(Vd, src1);
5503 } else if (u && opc == 0xD && sz == 0 && !q && !op1) {
5504 // vpadd.f32 Dd, Dn, Dm
5505 PairwiseAdd<float>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn);
5506 } else if (u && opc == 0xE && !op1) {
5507 // vcge/vcgt.f32 Qd, Qm, Qn
5508 bool ge = instr->Bit(21) == 0;
5509 float src1[4], src2[4];
5510 get_neon_register(Vn, src1);
5511 get_neon_register(Vm, src2);
5512 uint32_t dst[4];
5513 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5514 if (ge) {
5515 dst[i] = src1[i] >= src2[i] ? 0xFFFFFFFFu : 0;
5516 } else {
5517 dst[i] = src1[i] > src2[i] ? 0xFFFFFFFFu : 0;
5518 }
5519 }
5520 set_neon_register(Vd, dst);
5521 } else if (u && opc == 0xB) {
5522 // vqrdmulh.<dt> Qd, Qm, Qn
5523 NeonSize size = static_cast<NeonSize>(instr->Bits(21, 20));
5524 if (size == Neon16) {
5525 Binop<int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, SaturateRoundingQMul<int16_t>);
5526 } else {
5527 DCHECK_EQ(Neon32, size);
5528 Binop<int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm, Vn, SaturateRoundingQMul<int32_t>);
5529 }
5530 } else {
5531 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5532 }
5533 return;
5534 } else if (op0 == 1 && op1 == 0) {
5535 DecodeAdvancedSIMDTwoOrThreeRegisters(instr);
5536 } else if (op0 == 1 && op1 == 1) {
5537 // Advanced SIMD shifts and immediate generation.
5538 if (instr->Bits(21, 19) == 0 && instr->Bit(7) == 0) {
5539 VmovImmediate(this, instr);
5540 } else {
5541 // Advanced SIMD two registers and shift amount.
5542 int u = instr->Bit(24);
5543 int imm3H = instr->Bits(21, 19);
5544 int imm3L = instr->Bits(18, 16);
5545 int opc = instr->Bits(11, 8);
5546 int l = instr->Bit(7);
5547 int q = instr->Bit(6);
5548 int imm3H_L = imm3H << 1 | l;
5549 int imm7 = instr->Bits(21, 16);
5550 imm7 += (l << 6);
5551 int size = base::bits::RoundDownToPowerOfTwo32(imm7);
5552 NeonSize ns =
5553 static_cast<NeonSize>(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(size >> 3));
5554
5555 if (imm3H_L != 0 && opc == 0) {
5556 // vshr.s/u<size> Qd, Qm, shift
5557 int shift = 2 * size - imm7;
5558 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(q ? kSimd128Precision : kDoublePrecision);
5559 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(q ? kSimd128Precision : kDoublePrecision);
5560 switch (ns) {
5561 case Neon8:
5562 q ? ShiftRight<int8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u)
5563 : ShiftRight<int8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u);
5564 break;
5565 case Neon16:
5566 q ? ShiftRight<int16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u)
5567 : ShiftRight<int16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u);
5568 break;
5569 case Neon32:
5570 q ? ShiftRight<int32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u)
5571 : ShiftRight<int32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u);
5572 break;
5573 case Neon64:
5574 q ? ShiftRight<int64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u)
5575 : ShiftRight<int64_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift, u);
5576 break;
5577 }
5578 } else if (imm3H_L != 0 && opc == 1) {
5579 // vsra Dd, Dm, #imm
5580 DCHECK(!q); // Unimplemented for now.
5581 int shift = 2 * size - imm7;
5582 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5583 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5584 if (u) {
5585 switch (ns) {
5586 case Neon8:
5587 ShiftRightAccumulate<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5588 break;
5589 case Neon16:
5590 ShiftRightAccumulate<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5591 break;
5592 case Neon32:
5593 ShiftRightAccumulate<uint32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5594 break;
5595 case Neon64:
5596 ShiftRightAccumulate<uint64_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5597 break;
5598 }
5599 } else {
5600 switch (ns) {
5601 case Neon8:
5602 ArithmeticShiftRightAccumulate<int8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm,
5603 shift);
5604 break;
5605 case Neon16:
5606 ArithmeticShiftRightAccumulate<int16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm,
5607 shift);
5608 break;
5609 case Neon32:
5610 ArithmeticShiftRightAccumulate<int32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm,
5611 shift);
5612 break;
5613 case Neon64:
5614 ArithmeticShiftRightAccumulate<int64_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm,
5615 shift);
5616 break;
5617 }
5618 }
5619 } else if (imm3H_L != 0 && imm3L == 0 && opc == 0b1010 && !q) {
5620 if (u) {
5621 // vmovl unsigned
5622 if ((instr->VdValue() & 1) != 0) UNIMPLEMENTED();
5623 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5624 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5625 switch (imm3H) {
5626 case 1:
5627 Widen<uint8_t, uint16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5628 break;
5629 case 2:
5630 Widen<uint16_t, uint32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5631 break;
5632 case 4:
5633 Widen<uint32_t, uint64_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5634 break;
5635 default:
5636 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5637 }
5638 } else {
5639 // vmovl signed
5640 if ((instr->VdValue() & 1) != 0) UNIMPLEMENTED();
5641 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5642 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5643 switch (imm3H) {
5644 case 1:
5645 Widen<int8_t, int16_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5646 break;
5647 case 2:
5648 Widen<int16_t, int32_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5649 break;
5650 case 4:
5651 Widen<int32_t, int64_t>(this, Vd, Vm);
5652 break;
5653 default:
5654 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5655 }
5656 }
5657 } else if (!u && imm3H_L != 0 && opc == 0b0101) {
5658 // vshl.i<size> Qd, Qm, shift
5659 int shift = imm7 - size;
5660 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5661 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSimd128Precision);
5662 NeonSize ns =
5663 static_cast<NeonSize>(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(size >> 3));
5664 switch (ns) {
5665 case Neon8:
5666 ShiftLeft<uint8_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5667 break;
5668 case Neon16:
5669 ShiftLeft<uint16_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5670 break;
5671 case Neon32:
5672 ShiftLeft<uint32_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5673 break;
5674 case Neon64:
5675 ShiftLeft<uint64_t, kSimd128Size>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5676 break;
5677 }
5678 } else if (u && imm3H_L != 0 && opc == 0b0100) {
5679 // vsri.<size> Dd, Dm, shift
5680 int shift = 2 * size - imm7;
5681 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5682 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5683 switch (size) {
5684 case 8:
5685 ShiftRightAndInsert<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5686 break;
5687 case 16:
5688 ShiftRightAndInsert<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5689 break;
5690 case 32:
5691 ShiftRightAndInsert<uint32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5692 break;
5693 case 64:
5694 ShiftRightAndInsert<uint64_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5695 break;
5696 default:
5697 UNREACHABLE();
5698 }
5699 } else if (u && imm3H_L != 0 && opc == 0b0101) {
5700 // vsli.<size> Dd, Dm, shift
5701 int shift = imm7 - size;
5702 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5703 int Vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5704 switch (size) {
5705 case 8:
5706 ShiftLeftAndInsert<uint8_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5707 break;
5708 case 16:
5709 ShiftLeftAndInsert<uint16_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5710 break;
5711 case 32:
5712 ShiftLeftAndInsert<uint32_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5713 break;
5714 case 64:
5715 ShiftLeftAndInsert<uint64_t, kDoubleSize>(this, Vd, Vm, shift);
5716 break;
5717 default:
5718 UNREACHABLE();
5719 }
5720 }
5721 }
5722 return;
5723 }
5724}

5726void Simulator::DecodeMemoryHintsAndBarriers(Instruction* instr) {
5727 switch (instr->SpecialValue()) {
5728 case 0xA:
5729 case 0xB:
5730 if ((instr->Bits(22, 20) == 5) && (instr->Bits(15, 12) == 0xF)) {
5731 // pld: ignore instruction.
5732 } else if (instr->SpecialValue() == 0xA && instr->Bits(22, 20) == 7) {
5733 // dsb, dmb, isb: ignore instruction for now.
5734 // TODO(binji): implement
5735 // Also refer to the ARMv6 CP15 equivalents in DecodeTypeCP15.
5736 } else {
5737 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5738 }
5739 break;
5740 default:
5741 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5742 }

5744
5745void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStore(
5746 Instruction* instr) {
5747 int op0 = instr->Bit(23);
5748 int op1 = instr->Bits(11, 10);
5749
5750 if (!op0) {
5751 DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadStoreMultipleStructures(instr);
5752 } else if (op1 == 0b11) {
5753 DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadSingleStructureToAllLanes(instr);
5754 } else {
5755 DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadStoreSingleStructureToOneLane(instr);
5756 }
5757}
5758
5759void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadStoreMultipleStructures(
5760 Instruction* instr) {
5761 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5762 int Rn = instr->VnValue();
5763 int Rm = instr->VmValue();
5764 int type = instr->Bits(11, 8);
5765 int32_t address = get_register(Rn);
5766 int regs = 0;
5767 switch (type) {
5768 case nlt_1:
5769 regs = 1;
5770 break;
5771 case nlt_2:
5772 regs = 2;
5773 break;
5774 case nlt_3:
5775 regs = 3;
5776 break;
5777 case nlt_4:
5778 regs = 4;
5779 break;
5780 default:
5781 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5782 }
5783 if (instr->Bit(21)) {
5784 // vld1
5785 int r = 0;
5786 while (r < regs) {
5787 uint32_t data[2];
5788 data[0] = ReadW(address);
5789 data[1] = ReadW(address + 4);
5790 set_d_register(Vd + r, data);
5791 address += 8;
5792 r++;
5793 }
5794 } else {
5795 // vst1
5796 int r = 0;
5797 while (r < regs) {
5798 uint32_t data[2];
5799 get_d_register(Vd + r, data);
5800 WriteW(address, data[0]);
5801 WriteW(address + 4, data[1]);
5802 address += 8;
5803 r++;
5804 }
5805 }
5806 AdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStoreWriteback(Rn, Rm, 8 * regs);
5807}
5808
5809void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadSingleStructureToAllLanes(
5810 Instruction* instr) {
5811 DCHECK_NE(0, instr->Bit(21));
5812 int N = instr->Bits(9, 8);
5813
5814 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5815 int Rn = instr->VnValue();
5816 int Rm = instr->VmValue();
5817 int32_t address = get_register(Rn);
5818
5819 if (!N) {
5820 // vld1 (single element to all lanes).
5821 int regs = instr->Bit(5) + 1;
5822 int size = instr->Bits(7, 6);
5823 uint32_t q_data[2];
5824 switch (size) {
5825 case Neon8: {
5826 uint8_t data = ReadBU(address);
5827 uint8_t* dst = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(q_data);
5828 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
5829 dst[i] = data;
5830 }
5831 break;
5832 }
5833 case Neon16: {
5834 uint16_t data = ReadHU(address);
5835 uint16_t* dst = reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(q_data);
5836 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5837 dst[i] = data;
5838 }
5839 break;
5840 }
5841 case Neon32: {
5842 uint32_t data = ReadW(address);
5843 for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
5844 q_data[i] = data;
5845 }
5846 break;
5847 }
5848 }
5849 for (int r = 0; r < regs; r++) {
5850 set_neon_register<uint32_t, kDoubleSize>(Vd + r, q_data);
5851 }
5852 AdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStoreWriteback(Rn, Rm, 1 << size);
5853 } else {
5854 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5855 }
5856}
5857
5858void Simulator::DecodeAdvancedSIMDLoadStoreSingleStructureToOneLane(
5859 Instruction* instr) {
5860 int L = instr->Bit(21);
5861 int size = instr->Bits(11, 10);
5862 int N = instr->Bits(9, 8);
5863 int Vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5864 int Rn = instr->VnValue();
5865 int Rm = instr->VmValue();
5866 int32_t address = get_register(Rn);
5867
5868 if (L && N == 0) {
5869 // vld1 (single element to one lane)
5870 DCHECK_NE(3, size);
5871 uint64_t dreg;
5872 get_d_register(Vd, &dreg);
5873 switch (size) {
5874 case Neon8: {
5875 uint64_t data = ReadBU(address);
5876 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bit(4));
5877 int i = instr->Bits(7, 5) * 8;
5878 dreg = (dreg & ~(uint64_t{0xff} << i)) | (data << i);
5879 break;
5880 }
5881 case Neon16: {
5882 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bits(5, 4)); // Alignment not supported.
5883 uint64_t data = ReadHU(address);
5884 int i = instr->Bits(7, 6) * 16;
5885 dreg = (dreg & ~(uint64_t{0xffff} << i)) | (data << i);
5886 break;
5887 }
5888 case Neon32: {
5889 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bits(6, 4)); // Alignment not supported.
5890 uint64_t data = static_cast<unsigned>(ReadW(address));
5891 int i = instr->Bit(7) * 32;
5892 dreg = (dreg & ~(uint64_t{0xffffffff} << i)) | (data << i);
5893 break;
5894 }
5895 case Neon64: {
5896 // Should have been handled by vld1 (single element to all lanes).
5897 UNREACHABLE();
5898 }
5899 }
5900 set_d_register(Vd, &dreg);
5901 AdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStoreWriteback(Rn, Rm, 1 << size);
5902 } else if (!L && N == 0) {
5903 // vst1s (single element from one lane).
5904 DCHECK_NE(3, size);
5905 uint64_t dreg;
5906 get_d_register(Vd, &dreg);
5907 switch (size) {
5908 case Neon8: {
5909 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bit(4));
5910 int i = instr->Bits(7, 5) * 8;
5911 dreg = (dreg >> i) & 0xff;
5912 WriteB(address, static_cast<uint8_t>(dreg));
5913 break;
5914 }
5915 case Neon16: {
5916 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bits(5, 4)); // Alignment not supported.
5917 int i = instr->Bits(7, 6) * 16;
5918 dreg = (dreg >> i) & 0xffff;
5919 WriteH(address, static_cast<uint16_t>(dreg));
5920 break;
5921 }
5922 case Neon32: {
5923 DCHECK_EQ(0, instr->Bits(6, 4)); // Alignment not supported.
5924 int i = instr->Bit(7) * 32;
5925 dreg = (dreg >> i) & 0xffffffff;
5926 WriteW(address, base::bit_cast<int>(static_cast<uint32_t>(dreg)));
5927 break;
5928 }
5929 case Neon64: {
5930 // Should have been handled by vst1 (single element to all lanes).
5931 UNREACHABLE();
5932 }
5933 }
5934 AdvancedSIMDElementOrStructureLoadStoreWriteback(Rn, Rm, 1 << size);
5935 } else {
5936 UNIMPLEMENTED();
5937 }
5938}
5939
5940void Simulator::DecodeFloatingPointDataProcessing(Instruction* instr) {
5941 switch (instr->SpecialValue()) {
5942 case 0x1D:
5943 if (instr->Opc1Value() == 0x7 && instr->Opc3Value() == 0x1 &&
5944 instr->Bits(11, 9) == 0x5 && instr->Bits(19, 18) == 0x2) {
5945 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
5946 int vm = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5947 int vd = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
5948 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(vm).get_scalar();
5949 double dd_value = 0.0;
5950 int rounding_mode = instr->Bits(17, 16);
5951 switch (rounding_mode) {
5952 case 0x0: // vrinta - round with ties to away from zero
5953 dd_value = round(dm_value);
5954 break;
5955 case 0x1: { // vrintn - round with ties to even
5956 dd_value = nearbyint(dm_value);
5957 break;
5958 }
5959 case 0x2: // vrintp - ceil
5960 dd_value = ceil(dm_value);
5961 break;
5962 case 0x3: // vrintm - floor
5963 dd_value = floor(dm_value);
5964 break;
5965 default:
5966 UNREACHABLE(); // Case analysis is exhaustive.
5967 }
5968 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
5969 set_d_register_from_double(vd, dd_value);
5970 } else {
5971 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
5972 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
5973 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
5974 float sd_value = 0.0;
5975 int rounding_mode = instr->Bits(17, 16);
5976 switch (rounding_mode) {
5977 case 0x0: // vrinta - round with ties to away from zero
5978 sd_value = roundf(sm_value);
5979 break;
5980 case 0x1: { // vrintn - round with ties to even
5981 sd_value = nearbyintf(sm_value);
5982 break;
5983 }
5984 case 0x2: // vrintp - ceil
5985 sd_value = ceilf(sm_value);
5986 break;
5987 case 0x3: // vrintm - floor
5988 sd_value = floorf(sm_value);
5989 break;
5990 default:
5991 UNREACHABLE(); // Case analysis is exhaustive.
5992 }
5993 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
5994 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
5995 }
5996 } else if ((instr->Opc1Value() == 0x4) && (instr->Bits(11, 9) == 0x5) &&
5997 (instr->Bit(4) == 0x0)) {
5998 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
5999 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6000 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6001 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6002 double dn_value = get_double_from_d_register(n).get_scalar();
6003 double dm_value = get_double_from_d_register(m).get_scalar();
6004 double dd_value;
6005 if (instr->Bit(6) == 0x1) { // vminnm
6006 if ((dn_value < dm_value) || std::isnan(dm_value)) {
6007 dd_value = dn_value;
6008 } else if ((dm_value < dn_value) || std::isnan(dn_value)) {
6009 dd_value = dm_value;
6010 } else {
6011 DCHECK_EQ(dn_value, dm_value);
6012 // Make sure that we pick the most negative sign for +/-0.
6013 dd_value = std::signbit(dn_value) ? dn_value : dm_value;
6014 }
6015 } else { // vmaxnm
6016 if ((dn_value > dm_value) || std::isnan(dm_value)) {
6017 dd_value = dn_value;
6018 } else if ((dm_value > dn_value) || std::isnan(dn_value)) {
6019 dd_value = dm_value;
6020 } else {
6021 DCHECK_EQ(dn_value, dm_value);
6022 // Make sure that we pick the most positive sign for +/-0.
6023 dd_value = std::signbit(dn_value) ? dm_value : dn_value;
6024 }
6025 }
6026 dd_value = canonicalizeNaN(dd_value);
6027 set_d_register_from_double(d, dd_value);
6028 } else {
6029 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6030 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6031 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6032 float sn_value = get_float_from_s_register(n).get_scalar();
6033 float sm_value = get_float_from_s_register(m).get_scalar();
6034 float sd_value;
6035 if (instr->Bit(6) == 0x1) { // vminnm
6036 if ((sn_value < sm_value) || std::isnan(sm_value)) {
6037 sd_value = sn_value;
6038 } else if ((sm_value < sn_value) || std::isnan(sn_value)) {
6039 sd_value = sm_value;
6040 } else {
6041 DCHECK_EQ(sn_value, sm_value);
6042 // Make sure that we pick the most negative sign for +/-0.
6043 sd_value = std::signbit(sn_value) ? sn_value : sm_value;
6044 }
6045 } else { // vmaxnm
6046 if ((sn_value > sm_value) || std::isnan(sm_value)) {
6047 sd_value = sn_value;
6048 } else if ((sm_value > sn_value) || std::isnan(sn_value)) {
6049 sd_value = sm_value;
6050 } else {
6051 DCHECK_EQ(sn_value, sm_value);
6052 // Make sure that we pick the most positive sign for +/-0.
6053 sd_value = std::signbit(sn_value) ? sm_value : sn_value;
6054 }
6055 }
6056 sd_value = canonicalizeNaN(sd_value);
6057 set_s_register_from_float(d, sd_value);
6058 }
6059 } else {
6060 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6061 }
6062 break;
6063 case 0x1C:
6064 if ((instr->Bits(11, 9) == 0x5) && (instr->Bit(6) == 0) &&
6065 (instr->Bit(4) == 0)) {
6066 // VSEL* (floating-point)
6067 bool condition_holds;
6068 switch (instr->Bits(21, 20)) {
6069 case 0x0: // VSELEQ
6070 condition_holds = (z_flag_ == 1);
6071 break;
6072 case 0x1: // VSELVS
6073 condition_holds = (v_flag_ == 1);
6074 break;
6075 case 0x2: // VSELGE
6076 condition_holds = (n_flag_ == v_flag_);
6077 break;
6078 case 0x3: // VSELGT
6079 condition_holds = ((z_flag_ == 0) && (n_flag_ == v_flag_));
6080 break;
6081 default:
6082 UNREACHABLE(); // Case analysis is exhaustive.
6083 }
6084 if (instr->SzValue() == 0x1) {
6085 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6086 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6087 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kDoublePrecision);
6088 Float64 result = get_double_from_d_register(condition_holds ? n : m);
6089 set_d_register_from_double(d, result);
6090 } else {
6091 int n = instr->VFPNRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6092 int m = instr->VFPMRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6093 int d = instr->VFPDRegValue(kSinglePrecision);
6094 Float32 result = get_float_from_s_register(condition_holds ? n : m);
6095 set_s_register_from_float(d, result);
6096 }
6097 } else {
6098 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6099 }
6100 break;
6101 default:
6102 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6103 }
6104}
6105
6106void Simulator::DecodeSpecialCondition(Instruction* instr) {
6107 int op0 = instr->Bits(25, 24);
6108 int op1 = instr->Bits(11, 9);
6109 int op2 = instr->Bit(4);
6110
6111 if (instr->Bit(27) == 0) {
6112 DecodeUnconditional(instr);
6113 } else if ((instr->Bits(27, 26) == 0b11) && (op0 == 0b10) &&
6114 ((op1 >> 1) == 0b10) && !op2) {
6115 DecodeFloatingPointDataProcessing(instr);
6116 } else {
6117 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6118 }
6119}
6120
6121// Executes the current instruction.
6122void Simulator::InstructionDecode(Instruction* instr) {
6123 if (v8_flags.check_icache) {
6124 CheckICache(i_cache(), instr);
6125 }
6126 pc_modified_ = false;
6127 if (InstructionTracingEnabled()) {
6128 disasm::NameConverter converter;
6129 disasm::Disassembler dasm(converter);
6130 // use a reasonably large buffer
6131 v8::base::EmbeddedVector<char, 256> buffer;
6132 dasm.InstructionDecode(buffer, reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(instr));
6133 PrintF(" 0x%08" V8PRIxPTR " %s\n", reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(instr),
6134 buffer.begin());
6135 }
6136 if (instr->ConditionField() == kSpecialCondition) {
6137 DecodeSpecialCondition(instr);
6138 } else if (ConditionallyExecute(instr)) {
6139 switch (instr->TypeValue()) {
6140 case 0:
6141 case 1: {
6142 DecodeType01(instr);
6143 break;
6144 }
6145 case 2: {
6146 DecodeType2(instr);
6147 break;
6148 }
6149 case 3: {
6150 DecodeType3(instr);
6151 break;
6152 }
6153 case 4: {
6154 DecodeType4(instr);
6155 break;
6156 }
6157 case 5: {
6158 DecodeType5(instr);
6159 break;
6160 }
6161 case 6: {
6162 DecodeType6(instr);
6163 break;
6164 }
6165 case 7: {
6166 DecodeType7(instr);
6167 break;
6168 }
6169 default: {
6170 UNIMPLEMENTED();
6171 }
6172 }
6173 }
6174 if (!pc_modified_) {
6175 set_register(pc, reinterpret_cast<int32_t>(instr) + kInstrSize);
6176 }
6177}
6178
6179void Simulator::Execute() {
6180 // Get the PC to simulate. Cannot use the accessor here as we need the
6181 // raw PC value and not the one used as input to arithmetic instructions.
6182 int program_counter = get_pc();
6183
6184 if (v8_flags.stop_sim_at == 0) {
6185 // Fast version of the dispatch loop without checking whether the simulator
6186 // should be stopping at a particular executed instruction.
6187 while (program_counter != end_sim_pc) {
6188 Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(program_counter);
6189 icount_ = base::AddWithWraparound(icount_, 1);
6190 InstructionDecode(instr);
6191 program_counter = get_pc();
6192 }
6193 } else {
6194 // v8_flags.stop_sim_at is at the non-default value. Stop in the debugger
6195 // when we reach the particular instruction count.
6196 while (program_counter != end_sim_pc) {
6197 Instruction* instr = reinterpret_cast<Instruction*>(program_counter);
6198 icount_ = base::AddWithWraparound(icount_, 1);
6199 if (icount_ == v8_flags.stop_sim_at) {
6200 ArmDebugger dbg(this);
6201 dbg.Debug();
6202 } else {
6203 InstructionDecode(instr);
6204 }
6205 program_counter = get_pc();
6206 }
6207 }
6208}
6209
6210void Simulator::CallInternal(Address entry) {
6211 // Adjust JS-based stack limit to C-based stack limit.
6212 isolate_->stack_guard()->AdjustStackLimitForSimulator();
6213
6214 // Prepare to execute the code at entry
6215 set_register(pc, static_cast<int32_t>(entry));
6216 // Put down marker for end of simulation. The simulator will stop simulation
6217 // when the PC reaches this value. By saving the "end simulation" value into
6218 // the LR the simulation stops when returning to this call point.
6219 set_register(lr, end_sim_pc);
6220
6221 // Remember the values of callee-saved registers.
6222 // The code below assumes that r9 is not used as sb (static base) in
6223 // simulator code and therefore is regarded as a callee-saved register.
6224 int32_t r4_val = get_register(r4);
6225 int32_t r5_val = get_register(r5);
6226 int32_t r6_val = get_register(r6);
6227 int32_t r7_val = get_register(r7);
6228 int32_t r8_val = get_register(r8);
6229 int32_t r9_val = get_register(r9);
6230 int32_t r10_val = get_register(r10);
6231 int32_t r11_val = get_register(r11);
6232
6233 // Set up the callee-saved registers with a known value. To be able to check
6234 // that they are preserved properly across JS execution.
6235 int32_t callee_saved_value = icount_;
6236 set_register(r4, callee_saved_value);
6237 set_register(r5, callee_saved_value);
6238 set_register(r6, callee_saved_value);
6239 set_register(r7, callee_saved_value);
6240 set_register(r8, callee_saved_value);
6241 set_register(r9, callee_saved_value);
6242 set_register(r10, callee_saved_value);
6243 set_register(r11, callee_saved_value);
6244
6245 // Start the simulation
6246 Execute();
6247
6248 // Check that the callee-saved registers have been preserved.
6249 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r4));
6250 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r5));
6251 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r6));
6252 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r7));
6253 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r8));
6254 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r9));
6255 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r10));
6256 CHECK_EQ(callee_saved_value, get_register(r11));
6257
6258 // Restore callee-saved registers with the original value.
6259 set_register(r4, r4_val);
6260 set_register(r5, r5_val);
6261 set_register(r6, r6_val);
6262 set_register(r7, r7_val);
6263 set_register(r8, r8_val);
6264 set_register(r9, r9_val);
6265 set_register(r10, r10_val);
6266 set_register(r11, r11_val);
6267}
6268
6269intptr_t Simulator::CallImpl(Address entry, int argument_count,
6270 const intptr_t* arguments) {
6271 // Set up arguments
6272
6273 // First four arguments passed in registers.
6274 int reg_arg_count = std::min(4, argument_count);
6275 if (reg_arg_count > 0) set_register(r0, arguments[0]);
6276 if (reg_arg_count > 1) set_register(r1, arguments[1]);
6277 if (reg_arg_count > 2) set_register(r2, arguments[2]);
6278 if (reg_arg_count > 3) set_register(r3, arguments[3]);
6279
6280 // Remaining arguments passed on stack.
6281 int original_stack = get_register(sp);
6282 // Compute position of stack on entry to generated code.
6283 int entry_stack = (original_stack - (argument_count - 4) * sizeof(int32_t));
6284 if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() != 0) {
6285 entry_stack &= -base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6286 }
6287 // Store remaining arguments on stack, from low to high memory.
6288 memcpy(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t*>(entry_stack), arguments + reg_arg_count,
6289 (argument_count - reg_arg_count) * sizeof(*arguments));
6290 set_register(sp, entry_stack);
6291
6292 CallInternal(entry);
6293
6294 // Pop stack passed arguments.
6295 CHECK_EQ(entry_stack, get_register(sp));
6296 set_register(sp, original_stack);
6297
6298 return get_register(r0);
6299}
6300
6301intptr_t Simulator::CallFPImpl(Address entry, double d0, double d1) {
6302 if (use_eabi_hardfloat()) {
6303 set_d_register_from_double(0, d0);
6304 set_d_register_from_double(1, d1);
6305 } else {
6306 set_register_pair_from_double(0, &d0);
6307 set_register_pair_from_double(2, &d1);
6308 }
6309 CallInternal(entry);
6310 return get_register(r0);
6311}

6313uintptr_t Simulator::PushAddress(uintptr_t address) {
6314 int new_sp = get_register(sp) - sizeof(uintptr_t);
6315 uintptr_t* stack_slot = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(new_sp);
6316 *stack_slot = address;
6317 set_register(sp, new_sp);
6318 return new_sp;
6319}
6320
6321uintptr_t Simulator::PopAddress() {
6322 int current_sp = get_register(sp);
6323 uintptr_t* stack_slot = reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(current_sp);
6324 uintptr_t address = *stack_slot;
6325 set_register(sp, current_sp + sizeof(uintptr_t));
6326 return address;
6327}

6340void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyLoad(int32_t addr) {
6341 if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6342 // A load could cause a cache eviction which will affect the monitor. As a
6343 // result, it's most strict to unconditionally clear the local monitor on
6344 // load.
6345 Clear();
6346 }
6347}

6350 TransactionSize size) {
6351 access_state_ = MonitorAccess::Exclusive;
6352 tagged_addr_ = addr;
6353 size_ = size;
6354}
6355
6356void Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStore(int32_t addr) {
6357 if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6358 // It is implementation-defined whether a non-exclusive store to an address
6359 // covered by the local monitor during exclusive access transitions to open
6360 // or exclusive access. See ARM DDI 0406C.b, A3.4.1.
6361 //
6362 // However, a store could cause a cache eviction which will affect the
6363 // monitor. As a result, it's most strict to unconditionally clear the
6364 // local monitor on store.
6365 Clear();
6366 }
6367}
6368
6369bool Simulator::LocalMonitor::NotifyStoreExcl(int32_t addr,
6370 TransactionSize size) {
6371 if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6372 // It is allowed for a processor to require that the address matches
6373 // exactly (A3.4.5), so this comparison does not mask addr.
6374 if (addr == tagged_addr_ && size_ == size) {
6375 Clear();
6376 return true;
6377 } else {
6378 // It is implementation-defined whether an exclusive store to a
6379 // non-tagged address will update memory. Behavior is unpredictable if
6380 // the transaction size of the exclusive store differs from that of the
6381 // exclusive load. See ARM DDI 0406C.b, A3.4.5.
6382 Clear();
6383 return false;
6384 }
6385 } else {
6386 DCHECK(access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Open);
6387 return false;
6388 }
6389}

6398void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::Clear_Locked() {
6399 access_state_ = MonitorAccess::Open;
6400 tagged_addr_ = 0;
6401}
6402
6403void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(int32_t addr) {
6404 access_state_ = MonitorAccess::Exclusive;
6405 tagged_addr_ = addr;
6406}
6407
6408void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::NotifyStore_Locked(
6409 int32_t addr, bool is_requesting_processor) {
6410 if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6411 // It is implementation-defined whether a non-exclusive store by the
6412 // requesting processor to an address covered by the global monitor
6413 // during exclusive access transitions to open or exclusive access.
6414 //
6415 // For any other processor, the access state always transitions to open
6416 // access.
6417 //
6418 // See ARM DDI 0406C.b, A3.4.2.
6419 //
6420 // However, similar to the local monitor, it is possible that a store
6421 // caused a cache eviction, which can affect the montior, so
6422 // conservatively, we always clear the monitor.
6423 Clear_Locked();
6424 }
6425}
6426
6427bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::Processor::NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(
6428 int32_t addr, bool is_requesting_processor) {
6429 if (access_state_ == MonitorAccess::Exclusive) {
6430 if (is_requesting_processor) {
6431 // It is allowed for a processor to require that the address matches
6432 // exactly (A3.4.5), so this comparison does not mask addr.
6433 if (addr == tagged_addr_) {
6434 // The access state for the requesting processor after a successful
6435 // exclusive store is implementation-defined, but according to the ARM
6436 // DDI, this has no effect on the subsequent operation of the global
6437 // monitor.
6438 Clear_Locked();
6439 // Introduce occasional strex failures. This is to simulate the
6440 // behavior of hardware, which can randomly fail due to background
6441 // cache evictions.
6442 if (failure_counter_++ >= kMaxFailureCounter) {
6443 failure_counter_ = 0;
6444 return false;
6445 } else {
6446 return true;
6447 }
6448 }
6449 } else if ((addr & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask) ==
6450 (tagged_addr_ & kExclusiveTaggedAddrMask)) {
6451 // Check the masked addresses when responding to a successful lock by
6452 // another processor so the implementation is more conservative (i.e. the
6453 // granularity of locking is as large as possible.)
6454 Clear_Locked();
6455 return false;
6456 }
6457 }
6458 return false;
6459}
6460
6461void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(int32_t addr,
6462 Processor* processor) {
6463 processor->NotifyLoadExcl_Locked(addr);
6464 PrependProcessor_Locked(processor);
6465}
6466
6467void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStore_Locked(int32_t addr,
6468 Processor* processor) {
6469 // Notify each processor of the store operation.
6470 for (Processor* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
6471 bool is_requesting_processor = iter == processor;
6472 iter->NotifyStore_Locked(addr, is_requesting_processor);
6473 }
6474}
6475
6476bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(int32_t addr,
6477 Processor* processor) {
6478 DCHECK(IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(processor));
6479 if (processor->NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(addr, true)) {
6480 // Notify the other processors that this StoreExcl succeeded.
6481 for (Processor* iter = head_; iter; iter = iter->next_) {
6482 if (iter != processor) {
6483 iter->NotifyStoreExcl_Locked(addr, false);
6484 }
6485 }
6486 return true;
6487 } else {
6488 return false;
6489 }
6490}
6491
6492bool Simulator::GlobalMonitor::IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(
6493 Processor* processor) const {
6494 return head_ == processor || processor->next_ || processor->prev_;
6495}
6496
6497void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::PrependProcessor_Locked(Processor* processor) {
6498 if (IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(processor)) {
6499 return;
6500 }
6501
6502 if (head_) {
6503 head_->prev_ = processor;
6504 }
6505 processor->prev_ = nullptr;
6506 processor->next_ = head_;
6507 head_ = processor;
6508}
6509
6510void Simulator::GlobalMonitor::RemoveProcessor(Processor* processor) {
6511 base::MutexGuard lock_guard(&mutex);
6512 if (!IsProcessorInLinkedList_Locked(processor)) {
6513 return;
6514 }
6515
6516 if (processor->prev_) {
6517 processor->prev_->next_ = processor->next_;
6518 } else {
6519 head_ = processor->next_;
6520 }
6521 if (processor->next_) {
6522 processor->next_->prev_ = processor->prev_;
6523 }
6524 processor->prev_ = nullptr;
6525 processor->next_ = nullptr;
6526}

6536V8_DONT_STRIP_SYMBOL
6537V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE extern bool _v8_internal_Simulator_ExecDebugCommand(
6538 const char* command) {
6539 i::Isolate* isolate = i::Isolate::Current();
6540 if (!isolate) {
6541 fprintf(stderr, "No V8 Isolate found\n");
6542 return false;
6543 }
6544 i::Simulator* simulator = i::Simulator::current(isolate);
6545 if (!simulator) {
6546 fprintf(stderr, "No Arm simulator found\n");
6547 return false;
6548 }
6549 // Copy the command so that the simulator can take ownership of it.
6550 size_t len = strlen(command);
6551 i::ArrayUniquePtr<char> command_copy(i::NewArray<char>(len + 1));
6552 i::MemCopy(command_copy.get(), command, len + 1);
6553 return i::ArmDebugger(simulator).ExecDebugCommand(std::move(command_copy));
6554}
